KELVIN.name: kelvin
KELVIN.description: The kelvin is the base unit of temperature in the International System of Units (SI). The kelvin is the primary unit of temperature measurement for the physical sciences, but is often used in conjunction with the degree Celsius - which has the same magnitude - where 0 kelvin (called "Absolute Zero") corresponds to a temperature of -273.15°C. "Absolute Zero" is the equivalent -459.67°F.

A temperature of 0K is equal to 0R which is the equivalent of -273.15°C or -459.67°F.

BCO16.name: Bco16

MASK.name: mask

FLAGS.name: flags

STRING.name: string

PER RADIAN.name: per radian
PER RADIAN.description: The input is value that will be a ratio "per radian".

PER DEGREE.name: per degree
PER DEGREE.description: The input is value that will be a ratio "per degree".

KEYFRAMES.name: keyframe, keyframes

XYZ.name: XYZ
XYZ.description:
This unit signifies a 3 value struct with the values (all 32bit floats):
          
            
              x - a value representing an X position
            
            
              y - a value representing an Y position
            
            
              z - a value representing an Z position
            
          
          This struct unit is required by the following SimVars:
          
            STRUCT_BODY_ROTATION_ACCELERATION  
            STRUCT_BODY_ROTATION_VELOCITY  
            STRUCT_BODY_VELOCITY
            STRUCT_ENGINE_POSITION
            STRUCT_EYEPOINT_DYNAMIC_ANGLE
            STRUCT_EYEPOINT_DYNAMIC_OFFSET
            STRUCT_SURFACE_RELATIVE_VELOCITY
            STRUCT_WORLDVELOCITY
            STRUCT_WORLD_ACCELERATION
            STRUCT_WORLD_ROTATION_VELOCITY

PBH.name: PBH
PBH.description:
This unit signifies a 3 value struct with the values (all 32bit integers):
          
            pitch - the pitch value
            bank - the bank value
            heading - the heading value
          
          This struct unit is required by the following SimVars:
          
            LANDING_LIGHT_PBH
            STRUCT_PBH32

LATLONALTPBH.name: latlonaltpbh
LATLONALTPBH.description:
This unit signifies a 6 value struct with the values:
          
            lat - a latitude, expressed as a 64bit integer where the first 16bits are padding, the next 32bits are the integer value and the last 16bits are the fraction.
            lon - a longitude, expressed as 64bit integer where the lower 16bits are the fractional part, the upper 32 bits are the integer part and the rest is padding.
            alt - an alttude, expressed as a 64bit integer where the first 16bits are padding, the next 32bits are the integer value and the last 16bits are the fraction.
            pitch - the pitch value, expressed as 32bit integer
            bank - the bank value, expressed as 32bit integer
            heading - the heading value, expressed as 32bit integer
          
          This struct unit is required by the following SimVars:
          
            STRUCT_LATLONALTPBH

LATLONALT.name: latlonalt
LATLONALT.description:
This unit signifies a 6 value struct with the values:
          
            lat - a latitude, expressed as a 64bit integer where the first 16bits are padding, the next 32bits are the integer value and the last 16bits are the fraction.
            lon - a longitude, expressed as 64bit integer where the lower 16bits are the fractional part, the upper 32 bits are the integer part and the rest is padding.
            alt - an alttude, expressed as a 64bit integer where the first 16bits are padding, the next 32bits are the integer value and the last 16bits are the fraction.
          
          This struct unit is required by the following SimVars:
          
            ADF LATLONALT
            INNER_MARKER_LATLONALT
            MIDDLE_MARKER_LATLONALT
            NAV_DME_LATLONALT
            NAV_GS_LATLONALT
            NAV_VOR_LATLONALT
            OUTER_MARKER_LATLONALT
            STRUCT_LATLONALT

PID STRUCT.name: PID_STRUCT
PID STRUCT.description:
This unit signifies a 7 value struct containing PID controller state with the values (all 64bit floats):
          
            pid_p - the proportional value
            pid_i - the first integral value
            pid_i2 - the second integral value
            pid_d - the proportional value
            i_boundary - the first integral boundary value
            i2_boundary - the second integral boundary value
            d_boundary - the derivative boundary value
          
          This struct is returned by the following SimVars:
          
            STRUC_AIRSPEED_HOLD_PID_CONSTS
            STRUC_HEADING_HOLD_PID_CONSTS

POILIST.name: POIList
POILIST.description: This unit signifies that the returned value is an array of POI data. This unit is only used within the JS for HTML gauges.

GLASSCOCKPITSETTINGS.name: GlassCockpitSettings
GLASSCOCKPITSETTINGS.description:
This unit is only used when retrieving the cockpit struct within the JS for HTML gauges.
          For the contents of this struct, please see the section on the Glass Cockpit Settings Struct.

FUELLEVELS.name: FuelLevels
FUELLEVELS.description:
This unit is for retrieving the fuel levels of all tanks and will return a struct containing the following values (all 32bit floats):
          
            Center
            LeftMain
            RightMain
            LeftAux
            RightAux
            LeftTip
            RightTip
            Center2
            Center3
            External1
            External2

AUTOPILOT APPROACH IS LOCALIZER.name: AUTOPILOT APPROACH IS LOCALIZER

AUTOPILOT SPEED SETTING.name: AUTOPILOT SPEED SETTING

AUTOPILOT TAKEOFF POWER ACTIVE.name: AUTOPILOT TAKEOFF POWER ACTIVE
AUTOPILOT TAKEOFF POWER ACTIVE.description: Takeoff / Go Around power mode active

AUTOPILOT VERTICAL HOLD.name: AUTOPILOT VERTICAL HOLD
AUTOPILOT VERTICAL HOLD.description: True if autopilot vertical hold applied

ASSISTANCE TAKEOFF ENABLED.name: ASSISTANCE TAKEOFF ENABLED
ASSISTANCE TAKEOFF ENABLED.description: Returns whether takeoff assistance has been enabled or not.

AI ANTISTALL STATE.name: AI ANTISTALL STATE
AI ANTISTALL STATE.description: The current state of the AI anti-stall system.

AI AUTOTRIM ACTIVE.name: AI AUTOTRIM ACTIVE

AI AUTOTRIM ACTIVE AGAINST PLAYER.name: AI AUTOTRIM ACTIVE AGAINST PLAYER
AI AUTOTRIM ACTIVE AGAINST PLAYER.description: Returns whether the AI auto-trim system is enabled or not for AI controlled aircraft.

AI CONTROLS.name: AI CONTROLS
AI CONTROLS.description: Returns whether the AI control system is enabled or not.

AI CURSOR MODE ACTIVE.name: AI CURSOR MODE ACTIVE
AI CURSOR MODE ACTIVE.description: Returns whether the AI cursor mode is active or not.

DELEGATE CONTROLS TO AI.name: DELEGATE CONTROLS TO AI
DELEGATE CONTROLS TO AI.description: Returns whether the AI control system is active or not.

FLY ASSISTANT CANCEL DESTINATION.name: FLY ASSISTANT CANCEL DESTINATION
FLY ASSISTANT CANCEL DESTINATION.description: When set with any value this will cancel the current flight assistant destination.

FLY ASSISTANT CANCEL DESTINATION DISPLAY.name: FLY ASSISTANT CANCEL DESTINATION DISPLAY
FLY ASSISTANT CANCEL DESTINATION DISPLAY.description: When set with any value this will cancel the display of the current flight assistant destination.

FLY ASSISTANT COM AI LOCKED.name: FLY ASSISTANT COM AI LOCKED
FLY ASSISTANT COM AI LOCKED.description: Returns true when the copilot AI control is active and therefore COM AI is locked on active too.

FLY ASSISTANT HAVE DESTINATION.name: FLY ASSISTANT HAVE DESTINATION
FLY ASSISTANT HAVE DESTINATION.description: Returns true when a destination has been set in the flight assistant.

FLY ASSISTANT LANDING SPEED.name: FLY ASSISTANT LANDING SPEED
FLY ASSISTANT LANDING SPEED.description: Returns the POH range or an estimated value for this speed.

FLY ASSISTANT LANDING SPEED DISPLAY MODE.name: FLY ASSISTANT LANDING SPEED DISPLAY MODE
FLY ASSISTANT LANDING SPEED DISPLAY MODE.description: Returns the display mode of the speed, CSS side (only STALL SPEED is working and will turn red when below).
FLY ASSISTANT LANDING SPEED DISPLAY MODE.name_std: FLY ASSISTANT LANDING SPEED DISPLAY MODE

FLY ASSISTANT NEAREST COUNT.name: FLY ASSISTANT NEAREST COUNT
FLY ASSISTANT NEAREST COUNT.description: Number of elements in this category

FLY ASSISTANT NEAREST METADATA.name: FLY ASSISTANT NEAREST METADATA
FLY ASSISTANT NEAREST METADATA.description: Currently not used within the simulation.

FLY ASSISTANT NEAREST NAME.name: FLY ASSISTANT NEAREST NAME
FLY ASSISTANT NEAREST NAME.description: Returns the name of the element at the specified index.

FLY ASSISTANT NEAREST SELECTED.name: FLY ASSISTANT NEAREST SELECTED
FLY ASSISTANT NEAREST SELECTED.description: Returns the index of the currently selected element.

FLY ASSISTANT RIBBONS ACTIVE.name: FLY ASSISTANT RIBBONS ACTIVE
FLY ASSISTANT RIBBONS ACTIVE.description: Returns true when both ribbon assistances are active (taxi and landing), and can also be used to set them.

FLY ASSISTANT SET AS DESTINATION.name: FLY ASSISTANT SET AS DESTINATION
FLY ASSISTANT SET AS DESTINATION.description: When set with any value, it will set the selected element as the current destination.

FLY ASSISTANT STALL SPEED.name: FLY ASSISTANT STALL SPEED
FLY ASSISTANT STALL SPEED.description: Returns the flight assistant stall speed.

FLY ASSISTANT STALL SPEED DISPLAY MODE.name: FLY ASSISTANT STALL SPEED DISPLAY MODE
FLY ASSISTANT STALL SPEED DISPLAY MODE.description: Returns the flight assistant stall speed display mode.
FLY ASSISTANT STALL SPEED DISPLAY MODE.name_std: FLY ASSISTANT STALL SPEED DISPLAY MODE

FLY ASSISTANT TAKEOFF SPEED.name: FLY ASSISTANT TAKEOFF SPEED
FLY ASSISTANT TAKEOFF SPEED.description: Returns the flight assistant takeoff speed.

FLY ASSISTANT TAKEOFF SPEED DISPLAY MODE.name: FLY ASSISTANT TAKEOFF SPEED DISPLAY MODE
FLY ASSISTANT TAKEOFF SPEED DISPLAY MODE.description: Returns the flight assistant takeoff speed display mode.
FLY ASSISTANT TAKEOFF SPEED DISPLAY MODE.name_std: FLY ASSISTANT TAKEOFF SPEED DISPLAY MODE

FLY ASSISTANT TAKEOFF SPEED ESTIMATED.name: FLY ASSISTANT TAKEOFF SPEED ESTIMATED
FLY ASSISTANT TAKEOFF SPEED ESTIMATED.description: Can be set to override the estimated takeoff speed

AUTOBRAKES ACTIVE.name: AUTOBRAKES ACTIVE
AUTOBRAKES ACTIVE.description: Whether or not the AutoBrakes are currently active.

BRAKE LEFT POSITION EX1.name: BRAKE LEFT POSITION EX1
BRAKE LEFT POSITION EX1.description: Percent left brake, ignoring the effect of the parking brake.

BRAKE PARKING POSITION.name: BRAKE PARKING POSITION
BRAKE PARKING POSITION.description: Sets the parking brake position to on (true) or off (false).

BRAKE RIGHT POSITION EX1.name: BRAKE RIGHT POSITION EX1
BRAKE RIGHT POSITION EX1.description: Percent right brake, ignoring the effect of the parking brake.

TOE BRAKES AVAILABLE.name: TOE BRAKES AVAILABLE
TOE BRAKES AVAILABLE.description: True if toe brakes are available

CONTACT POINT COMPRESSION.name: CONTACT POINT COMPRESSION:index
CONTACT POINT COMPRESSION.description: The percentage value representing the amount the contact point is compressed. Index is from 0-19.

CONTACT POINT IS ON GROUND.name: CONTACT POINT IS ON GROUND:index
CONTACT POINT IS ON GROUND.description: Returns true if the indexed contact point is on the ground, or will return false otherwise. Index is from 0 - 19.

CONTACT POINT IS SKIDDING.name: CONTACT POINT IS SKIDDING:index
CONTACT POINT IS SKIDDING.description: Returns true if the indexed contact point is skidding, or will return false otherwise. Index is from 0 - 19.

CONTACT POINT POSITION.name: CONTACT POINT POSITION:index
CONTACT POINT POSITION.description: The currently extended position of the (retractable) contact point, expressed as a percentage. Index is from 0 - 19.

CONTACT POINT SKIDDING FACTOR.name: CONTACT POINT SKIDDING FACTOR:index
CONTACT POINT SKIDDING FACTOR.description: The skidding factor associated with the indexed contact point, from 0 to 1. Index is from 0 - 19.

CONTACT POINT WATER DEPTH.name: CONTACT POINT WATER DEPTH:index
CONTACT POINT WATER DEPTH.description: This returns the depth of the water for the indexed contact point. Index is from 0 - 19.

AUX WHEEL ROTATION ANGLE.name: AUX WHEEL ROTATION ANGLE
AUX WHEEL ROTATION ANGLE.description: Aux wheel rotation angle (rotation around the axis for the wheel).

AUX WHEEL RPM.name: AUX WHEEL RPM
AUX WHEEL RPM.description: Rpm of fourth set of gear wheels.

CENTER WHEEL ROTATION ANGLE.name: CENTER WHEEL ROTATION ANGLE
CENTER WHEEL ROTATION ANGLE.description: Center wheel rotation angle (rotation around the axis for the wheel).

GEAR AUX STEER ANGLE.name: GEAR AUX STEER ANGLE
GEAR AUX STEER ANGLE.description: Aux wheel angle, negative to the left, positive to the right. The aux wheel is the fourth set of gear, sometimes used on helicopters.

GEAR AUX STEER ANGLE PCT.name: GEAR AUX STEER ANGLE PCT
GEAR AUX STEER ANGLE PCT.description: Aux steer angle as a percentage.

GEAR CENTER STEER ANGLE.name: GEAR CENTER STEER ANGLE
GEAR CENTER STEER ANGLE.description: Center wheel angle, negative to the left, positive to the right.

GEAR CENTER STEER ANGLE PCT.name: GEAR CENTER STEER ANGLE PCT
GEAR CENTER STEER ANGLE PCT.description: Center steer angle as a percentage.

GEAR DAMAGE BY SPEED.name: GEAR DAMAGE BY SPEED
GEAR DAMAGE BY SPEED.description: True if gear has been damaged by excessive speed.

GEAR EMERGENCY HANDLE POSITION.name: GEAR EMERGENCY HANDLE POSITION
GEAR EMERGENCY HANDLE POSITION.description: True if gear emergency handle applied.

GEAR HANDLE POSITION.name: GEAR HANDLE POSITION
GEAR HANDLE POSITION.description: True if gear handle is applied.

GEAR IS ON GROUND.name: GEAR IS ON GROUND:index
GEAR IS ON GROUND.description: True if the gear is on the ground.

GEAR IS SKIDDING.name: GEAR IS SKIDDING:index
GEAR IS SKIDDING.description: True if the gear is skidding.

GEAR LEFT STEER ANGLE.name: GEAR LEFT STEER ANGLE
GEAR LEFT STEER ANGLE.description: Left wheel angle, negative to the left, positive to the right.

GEAR LEFT STEER ANGLE PCT.name: GEAR LEFT STEER ANGLE PCT
GEAR LEFT STEER ANGLE PCT.description: Left steer angle as a percentage.

GEAR RIGHT STEER ANGLE.name: GEAR RIGHT STEER ANGLE
GEAR RIGHT STEER ANGLE.description: Right wheel angle, negative to the left, positive to the right.

GEAR RIGHT STEER ANGLE PCT.name: GEAR RIGHT STEER ANGLE PCT
GEAR RIGHT STEER ANGLE PCT.description: Right steer angle as a percentage.

GEAR SPEED EXCEEDED.name: GEAR SPEED EXCEEDED
GEAR SPEED EXCEEDED.description: True if safe speed limit for gear exceeded.

GEAR STEER ANGLE.name: GEAR STEER ANGLE:index
GEAR STEER ANGLE.description:
Alternative method of getting the steer angle. Index is one of the following:
          
            0 = center
            1 = left
            2 = right
            3 = aux

GEAR STEER ANGLE PCT.name: GEAR STEER ANGLE PCT:index
GEAR STEER ANGLE PCT.description:
Alternative method of getting steer angle as a percentage. Index is one of the following:
          
            0 = center
            1 = left
            2 = right
            3 = aux

GEAR WARNING.name: GEAR WARNING:index
GEAR WARNING.description:
Gear warnings. Index can be one of the following:
          
            0 = unknown
            1 = normal
            2 = amphib
GEAR WARNING.units:
Enum:
          
            0 = None
            1 = Gear Up
            2 = Amphibious Gear Up
            3 = Amphibious Gear Down
            4 = On Ground Handle Up

GEAR WATER DEPTH.name: GEAR WATER DEPTH
GEAR WATER DEPTH.description: The depth of the gear in the water.

IS GEAR FLOATS.name: IS GEAR FLOATS
IS GEAR FLOATS.description: True if landing gear are floats

IS GEAR RETRACTABLE.name: IS GEAR RETRACTABLE
IS GEAR RETRACTABLE.description: True if gear can be retracted

IS GEAR SKIDS.name: IS GEAR SKIDS
IS GEAR SKIDS.description: True if landing gear is skids

IS GEAR SKIS.name: IS GEAR SKIS
IS GEAR SKIS.description: True if landing gear is skis

IS GEAR WHEELS.name: IS GEAR WHEELS
IS GEAR WHEELS.description: True if landing gear is wheels

LEFT WHEEL ROTATION ANGLE.name: LEFT WHEEL ROTATION ANGLE
LEFT WHEEL ROTATION ANGLE.description: Left wheel rotation angle (rotation around the axis for the wheel).

NOSEWHEEL LOCK ON.name: NOSEWHEEL LOCK ON
NOSEWHEEL LOCK ON.description: True if the nosewheel lock is engaged.

REJECTED TAKEOFF BRAKES ACTIVE.name: REJECTED TAKEOFF BRAKES ACTIVE
REJECTED TAKEOFF BRAKES ACTIVE.description: Whether or not the rejected takeoff brakes are currently active.

RETRACT FLOAT SWITCH.name: RETRACT FLOAT SWITCH
RETRACT FLOAT SWITCH.description: True if retract float switch on

RETRACT LEFT FLOAT EXTENDED.name: RETRACT LEFT FLOAT EXTENDED
RETRACT LEFT FLOAT EXTENDED.units:
Percent
          (0 is fully retracted, 100 is fully extended)

RETRACT RIGHT FLOAT EXTENDED.name: RETRACT RIGHT FLOAT EXTENDED
RETRACT RIGHT FLOAT EXTENDED.units:
Percent
          (0 is fully retracted, 100 is fully extended)

RIGHT WHEEL ROTATION ANGLE.name: RIGHT WHEEL ROTATION ANGLE
RIGHT WHEEL ROTATION ANGLE.description: Right wheel rotation angle (rotation around the axis for the wheel).

WATER LEFT RUDDER STEER ANGLE.name: WATER LEFT RUDDER STEER ANGLE
WATER LEFT RUDDER STEER ANGLE.description: Water left rudder angle, negative to the left, positive to the right.

WATER LEFT RUDDER STEER ANGLE PCT.name: WATER LEFT RUDDER STEER ANGLE PCT
WATER LEFT RUDDER STEER ANGLE PCT.description: Water left rudder angle as a percentage.
WATER LEFT RUDDER STEER ANGLE PCT.name_std: WATER LEFT RUDDER STEER ANGLE PCT

WATER RIGHT RUDDER STEER ANGLE.name: WATER RIGHT RUDDER STEER ANGLE
WATER RIGHT RUDDER STEER ANGLE.description: Water right rudder angle, negative to the left, positive to the right.

WATER RIGHT RUDDER STEER ANGLE PCT.name: WATER RIGHT RUDDER STEER ANGLE PCT
WATER RIGHT RUDDER STEER ANGLE PCT.description: Water right rudder as a percentage.
WATER RIGHT RUDDER STEER ANGLE PCT.name_std: WATER RIGHT RUDDER STEER ANGLE PCT

WATER RUDDER HANDLE POSITION.name: WATER RUDDER HANDLE POSITION
WATER RUDDER HANDLE POSITION.description: Position of the water rudder handle (0 handle retracted, 100 rudder handle applied).

WHEEL ROTATION ANGLE.name: WHEEL ROTATION ANGLE:index
WHEEL ROTATION ANGLE.description:
Wheel rotation angle (rotation around the axis for the wheel). Index is one of the following:
          
            0 = center
            1 = left
            2 = right
            3 = aux

WHEEL RPM.name: WHEEL RPM:index
WHEEL RPM.description:
Wheel rpm. Index is one of the following:
          
            0 = center
            1 = left
            2 = right
            3 = aux

AILERON TRIM DISABLED.name: AILERON TRIM DISABLED
AILERON TRIM DISABLED.description: Whether or not the Aileron Trim has been disabled.

AILERON TRIM PCT.name: AILERON TRIM PCT
AILERON TRIM PCT.description: The trim position of the ailerons. Zero is fully retracted.

ELEVATOR TRIM DISABLED.name: ELEVATOR TRIM DISABLED
ELEVATOR TRIM DISABLED.description: Whether or not the Elevator Trim has been disabled.

FLAP DAMAGE BY SPEED.name: FLAP DAMAGE BY SPEED
FLAP DAMAGE BY SPEED.description: True if flaps are damaged by excessive speed.

FLAP POSITION SET.name: FLAP POSITION SET
FLAP POSITION SET.description: Set the position of the flaps control.

FLAP SPEED EXCEEDED.name: FLAP SPEED EXCEEDED
FLAP SPEED EXCEEDED.description: True if safe speed limit for flaps exceeded.

FLAPS EFFECTIVE HANDLE INDEX.name: FLAPS EFFECTIVE HANDLE INDEX
FLAPS EFFECTIVE HANDLE INDEX.description: This returns the effective flaps handle index, after some of the conditions have potentially forced the state to change.

LEADING EDGE FLAPS LEFT ANGLE.name: LEADING EDGE FLAPS LEFT ANGLE
LEADING EDGE FLAPS LEFT ANGLE.description: Angle left leading edge flap extended. Use LEADING_EDGE_FLAPS_LEFT_PERCENT to set a value.

LEADING EDGE FLAPS LEFT INDEX.name: LEADING EDGE FLAPS LEFT INDEX
LEADING EDGE FLAPS LEFT INDEX.description: Index of left leading edge flap position.

LEADING EDGE FLAPS LEFT PERCENT.name: LEADING EDGE FLAPS LEFT PERCENT
LEADING EDGE FLAPS LEFT PERCENT.description: Percent left leading edge flap extended.

LEADING EDGE FLAPS RIGHT ANGLE.name: LEADING EDGE FLAPS RIGHT ANGLE
LEADING EDGE FLAPS RIGHT ANGLE.description: Angle right leading edge flap extended. Use LEADING_EDGE_FLAPS_RIGHT_PERCENT to set a value.

LEADING EDGE FLAPS RIGHT INDEX.name: LEADING EDGE FLAPS RIGHT INDEX
LEADING EDGE FLAPS RIGHT INDEX.description: Index of right leading edge flap position.

LEADING EDGE FLAPS RIGHT PERCENT.name: LEADING EDGE FLAPS RIGHT PERCENT
LEADING EDGE FLAPS RIGHT PERCENT.description: Percent right leading edge flap extended.

TRAILING EDGE FLAPS LEFT ANGLE.name: TRAILING EDGE FLAPS LEFT ANGLE
TRAILING EDGE FLAPS LEFT ANGLE.description: Angle left trailing edge flap extended. Use TRAILING_EDGE_FLAPS_LEFT_PERCENT to set a value.

TRAILING EDGE FLAPS LEFT INDEX.name: TRAILING EDGE FLAPS LEFT INDEX
TRAILING EDGE FLAPS LEFT INDEX.description: Index of left trailing edge flap position.

TRAILING EDGE FLAPS LEFT PERCENT.name: TRAILING EDGE FLAPS LEFT PERCENT
TRAILING EDGE FLAPS LEFT PERCENT.description: Percent left trailing edge flap extended.

TRAILING EDGE FLAPS RIGHT ANGLE.name: TRAILING EDGE FLAPS RIGHT ANGLE
TRAILING EDGE FLAPS RIGHT ANGLE.description: Angle right trailing edge flap extended. Use TRAILING_EDGE_FLAPS_RIGHT_PERCENT to set a value.

TRAILING EDGE FLAPS RIGHT INDEX.name: TRAILING EDGE FLAPS RIGHT INDEX
TRAILING EDGE FLAPS RIGHT INDEX.description: Index of right trailing edge flap position.

TRAILING EDGE FLAPS RIGHT PERCENT.name: TRAILING EDGE FLAPS RIGHT PERCENT
TRAILING EDGE FLAPS RIGHT PERCENT.description: Percent right trailing edge flap extended.

FLY BY WIRE ALPHA PROTECTION.name: FLY BY WIRE ALPHA PROTECTION
FLY BY WIRE ALPHA PROTECTION.description: Returns true if the fly-by-wire alpha protection is enabled or false otherwise.

FLY BY WIRE ELAC FAILED.name: FLY BY WIRE ELAC FAILED
FLY BY WIRE ELAC FAILED.description: True if the Elevators and Ailerons computer has failed.

FLY BY WIRE ELAC SWITCH.name: FLY BY WIRE ELAC SWITCH
FLY BY WIRE ELAC SWITCH.description: True if the fly by wire Elevators and Ailerons computer is on.

FLY BY WIRE FAC FAILED.name: FLY BY WIRE FAC FAILED
FLY BY WIRE FAC FAILED.description: True if the Flight Augmentation computer has failed.

FLY BY WIRE FAC SWITCH.name: FLY BY WIRE FAC SWITCH
FLY BY WIRE FAC SWITCH.description: True if the fly by wire Flight Augmentation computer is on.

FLY BY WIRE SEC FAILED.name: FLY BY WIRE SEC FAILED
FLY BY WIRE SEC FAILED.description: True if the Spoilers and Elevators computer has failed.

FLY BY WIRE SEC SWITCH.name: FLY BY WIRE SEC SWITCH
FLY BY WIRE SEC SWITCH.description: True if the fly by wire Spoilers and Elevators computer is on.

FOLDING WING HANDLE POSITION.name: FOLDING WING HANDLE POSITION
FOLDING WING HANDLE POSITION.description: True if the folding wing handle is engaged.

FOLDING WING LEFT PERCENT.name: FOLDING WING LEFT PERCENT
FOLDING WING LEFT PERCENT.description: Left folding wing position, 1.0 is fully folded.

FOLDING WING RIGHT PERCENT.name: FOLDING WING RIGHT PERCENT
FOLDING WING RIGHT PERCENT.description: Right folding wing position, 1.0 is fully folded.

COLLECTIVE POSITION.name: COLLECTIVE POSITION
COLLECTIVE POSITION.description: The position of the helicopter's collective. 0 is fully up, 100 fully depressed.

RUDDER PEDAL POSITION.name: RUDDER PEDAL POSITION
RUDDER PEDAL POSITION.units:
Position (-16K to 0)
          -16K = left pedal pushed full in

RUDDER TRIM DISABLED.name: RUDDER TRIM DISABLED
RUDDER TRIM DISABLED.description: Whether or not the Rudder Trim has been disabled.

RUDDER TRIM PCT.name: RUDDER TRIM PCT
RUDDER TRIM PCT.description: The trim position of the rudder. Zero is no trim.

SPOILERS ARMED.name: SPOILERS ARMED
SPOILERS ARMED.description: Checks if autospoilers are armed (true) or not (false).

SPOILERS HANDLE POSITION.name: SPOILERS HANDLE POSITION
SPOILERS HANDLE POSITION.units:
Percent Over 100
          or
          Position
          (16K = down, 0 = up)

SPOILERS LEFT POSITION.name: SPOILERS LEFT POSITION
SPOILERS LEFT POSITION.units:
Percent Over 100
          or
          Position
          (0 = retracted, 16K fully extended)

SPOILERS RIGHT POSITION.name: SPOILERS RIGHT POSITION
SPOILERS RIGHT POSITION.units:
Percent Over 100
          or
          Position (0 = retracted, 16K fully extended)

BLAST SHIELD POSITION.name: BLAST SHIELD POSITION
BLAST SHIELD POSITION.description: Indexed from 1, 100 is fully deployed, 0 flat on deck

CABLE CAUGHT BY TAILHOOK.name: CABLE CAUGHT BY TAILHOOK
CABLE CAUGHT BY TAILHOOK.description: A number 1 through 4 for the cable number caught by the tailhook. Cable 1 is the one closest to the stern of the carrier. A value of 0 indicates no cable was caught.

CATAPULT STROKE POSITION.name: CATAPULT STROKE POSITION
CATAPULT STROKE POSITION.description: Catapults are indexed from 1. This value will be 0 before the catapult fires, and then up to 100 as the aircraft is propelled down the catapult. The aircraft may takeoff before the value reaches 100 (depending on the aircraft weight, power applied, and other factors), in which case this value will not be further updated. This value could be used to drive a bogie animation.

HOLDBACK BAR INSTALLED.name: HOLDBACK BAR INSTALLED
HOLDBACK BAR INSTALLED.description: Holdback bars allow build up of thrust before takeoff from a catapult, and are installed by the deck crew of an aircraft carrier.

LAUNCHBAR HELD EXTENDED.name: LAUNCHBAR HELD EXTENDED
LAUNCHBAR HELD EXTENDED.description: This will be True if the launchbar is fully extended, and can be used, for example, to change the color of an instrument light.

LAUNCHBAR POSITION.name: LAUNCHBAR POSITION
LAUNCHBAR POSITION.description: Installed on aircraft before takeoff from a carrier catapult. Note that gear cannot retract with this extended. 100 = fully extended. Refer to the document Notes on Aircraft Systems.

LAUNCHBAR SWITCH.name: LAUNCHBAR SWITCH
LAUNCHBAR SWITCH.description: If this is set to True the launch bar switch has been engaged.

NUMBER OF CATAPULTS.name: NUMBER OF CATAPULTS
NUMBER OF CATAPULTS.description: Maximum of 4. A model can contain more than 4 catapults, but only the first four will be read and recognized by the simulation.

CONCORDE NOSE ANGLE.name: CONCORDE NOSE ANGLE
CONCORDE NOSE ANGLE.description: The nose angle, where 0 is fully up.

CONCORDE VISOR NOSE HANDLE.name: CONCORDE VISOR NOSE HANDLE
CONCORDE VISOR NOSE HANDLE.units:
Enum:
          
            0:[index] visor up, nose down
            1:[index] visor down, nose up
            2:[index] visor down, nose 5 degrees
            3:[index] visor down, nose 12.5 degrees

CONCORDE VISOR POSITION PERCENT.name: CONCORDE VISOR POSITION PERCENT
CONCORDE VISOR POSITION PERCENT.description: The visor position expressed as a percentage where 0.0 = up and 1.0 = extended/down.

BUS LOOKUP INDEX.name: BUS LOOKUP INDEX
BUS LOOKUP INDEX.description:
This is a settable simvar meaning that it can both be read and set. Some of the simvars in this list are using this to lookup a value using two arguments (one argument in addition to the component index). For example to check the state of the connection between a "circuit.45" and the "bus.2" it would be written as follows:
          2 (>A:BUS LOOKUP INDEX, Number) (A:CIRCUIT CONNECTION ON:45, Bool)

BUS BREAKER PULLED.name: BUS BREAKER PULLED
BUS BREAKER PULLED.description: This will be true if the bus breaker is pulled. Requires a BUS_LOOKUP_INDEX and a bus index.

BUS CONNECTION ON.name: BUS CONNECTION ON
BUS CONNECTION ON.description: This will be true if the bus is connected. Requires a BUS_LOOKUP_INDEX and a bus index.

ELECTRICAL GENALT LOAD.name: ELECTRICAL GENALT LOAD
ELECTRICAL GENALT LOAD.description: This returns the percentage of the load output that is being consumed. This requires an alternator index when referencing.

ELECTRICAL GENALT BUS AMPS.name: ELECTRICAL GENALT BUS AMPS
ELECTRICAL GENALT BUS AMPS.description: The load handled by the alternator. This requires an alternator index when referencing.

ELECTRICAL GENALT BUS VOLTAGE.name: ELECTRICAL GENALT BUS VOLTAGE
ELECTRICAL GENALT BUS VOLTAGE.description: General alternator voltage. This requires an alternator index when referencing.

ELECTRICAL MAIN BUS VOLTAGE.name: ELECTRICAL MAIN BUS VOLTAGE
ELECTRICAL MAIN BUS VOLTAGE.description: The main bus voltage. Use a bus index when referencing.

ELECTRICAL OLD CHARGING AMPS.name: ELECTRICAL OLD CHARGING AMPS
ELECTRICAL OLD CHARGING AMPS.description:
Deprecated, do not use!
          Use ELECTRICAL BATTERY LOAD.

NEW ELECTRICAL SYSTEM.name: NEW ELECTRICAL SYSTEM
NEW ELECTRICAL SYSTEM.description: Is the aircraft using the new Electrical System or the legacy FSX one

ALTERNATOR BREAKER PULLED.name: ALTERNATOR BREAKER PULLED
ALTERNATOR BREAKER PULLED.description: This will be true if the alternator breaker is pulled. Requires a BUS_LOOKUP_INDEX and an alternator index.

ALTERNATOR CONNECTION ON.name: ALTERNATOR CONNECTION ON
ALTERNATOR CONNECTION ON.description: This will be true if the alternator is connected. Requires a BUS_LOOKUP_INDEX and an alternator index.

GENERAL ENG MASTER ALTERNATOR.name: GENERAL ENG MASTER ALTERNATOR:index
GENERAL ENG MASTER ALTERNATOR.description: The alternator (generator) switch position, true if the switch is ON. Requires an engine index, and the use of an alternator index when referencing.

APU BLEED PRESSURE RECEIVED BY ENGINE.name: APU BLEED PRESSURE RECEIVED BY ENGINE
APU BLEED PRESSURE RECEIVED BY ENGINE.description: Boolean, Whether or not the engine receives Bleed air from the APU.
APU BLEED PRESSURE RECEIVED BY ENGINE.name_std: APU BLEED PRESSURE RECEIVED BY ENGINE

APU GENERATOR ACTIVE.name: APU GENERATOR ACTIVE:index
APU GENERATOR ACTIVE.description: Set or get whether an APU is active (true) or not (false). Takes an index to be able to have multiple generators on a single APU.

APU GENERATOR SWITCH.name: APU GENERATOR SWITCH:index
APU GENERATOR SWITCH.description: Enables or disables the APU for an engine. Takes an index to be able to have multiple generators on a single APU

TURB ENG BLEED AIR.description: Bleed air pressure for the indexed engine (see note).

TURB ENG COMMANDED N1.description: Effective commanded N1 for the indexed turbine engine (see note).

TURB ENG CONDITION LEVER POSITION.name: TURB ENG CONDITION LEVER POSITION:index
TURB ENG CONDITION LEVER POSITION.description:
When the throttle is on idle position, this sets the condition levers to one of 3 positions to define the idle N1 target for the indexed engine (see note):
          
            Down position is the cut-off position that cuts the fuel to the engine, effectively shutting down the engine.
            Middle position requires N1 to reach the low idle value when throttle is in idle position (low idle value can be checked using the TURB_ENG_LOW_IDLE SimVar).
            High position requires N1 to reach the high idle value when throttle is in idle position (high idle value can be checked using the TURB_ENG_HIGH_IDLE SimVar).
          
          Note that this option requires several settings from the engines.cfg file to be set to specific values before working correctly:
          
            DisableMixtureControls needs to be set to 1 (TRUE).
            tp_idle_range should be set to 0 (since there is no mixture setting).
            idle_fuel_flow and idle_high_fuel_flow must be set to the same value (since there is no mixture setting to induce a variation between the 2).
            low_idle_n1 and high_idle_n1 to be correctly set.
TURB ENG CONDITION LEVER POSITION.units:
Enum:
          
            0 = fuel cut-off
            1 = low idle
            2 = high idle

DESIGN CRUISE ALT.name: DESIGN CRUISE ALT
DESIGN CRUISE ALT.description: This design constant represents the optimal altitude the aircraft should maintain when in cruise. It is derived from the cruise_alt setting in the [REFERENCE SPEEDS] section of the flightmodel.cfg. Default is 1500ft.

DESIGN SPAWN ALTITUDE CRUISE.name: DESIGN SPAWN ALTITUDE CRUISE
DESIGN SPAWN ALTITUDE CRUISE.description: This design constant represents the spawn altitude for the aircraft when spawning in cruise. It is derived from the spawn_cruise_altitude setting in the [REFERENCE SPEEDS] section of the flightmodel.cfg. Default is 1500ft.

DESIGN SPAWN ALTITUDE DESCENT.name: DESIGN SPAWN ALTITUDE DESCENT
DESIGN SPAWN ALTITUDE DESCENT.description: This design constant represents the spawn altitude for the aircraft when spawning in descent. It is derived from the spawn_descent_altitude setting in the [REFERENCE SPEEDS] section of the flightmodel.cfg. Default is 500ft.

DESIGN SPEED CLIMB.name: DESIGN SPEED CLIMB
DESIGN SPEED CLIMB.description: This design constant represents the optimal climb speed for the aircraft. It is derived from the climb_speed setting in the [REFERENCE SPEEDS] section of the flightmodel.cfg. Default value is -1.

DESIGN SPEED MIN ROTATION.name: DESIGN SPEED MIN ROTATION
DESIGN SPEED MIN ROTATION.description: This design constant represents the minimum speed required for aircraft rotation. It is derived from the rotation_speed_min setting in the [REFERENCE SPEEDS] section of the flightmodel.cfg. Default value is -1.

DESIGN SPEED VC.name: DESIGN SPEED VC
DESIGN SPEED VC.description: This design constant represents the aircraft ideal cruising speed. It is derived from the cruise_speed setting in the [REFERENCE SPEEDS] section of the flightmodel.cfg. The default value is computed an internal function that uses the estimated cruise altitude and estimated cruise percent power, according of the engine type, the number of engines, the density, the wing area and some drag parameters. Normally this value is set in the CFG file and the default value is never used.

DESIGN SPEED VS0.name: DESIGN SPEED VS0
DESIGN SPEED VS0.description: This design constant represents the the stall speed when flaps are fully extended. It is derived from the full_flaps_stall_speed setting in the [REFERENCE SPEEDS] section of the flightmodel.cfg. Default value is 0.8 x VS.

DESIGN SPEED VS1.name: DESIGN SPEED VS1
DESIGN SPEED VS1.description: This design constant represents the stall speed when flaps are fully retracted. It is derived from the flaps_up_stall_speed setting in the [REFERENCE SPEEDS] section of the flightmodel.cfg. Default value is 0.

DESIGN TAKEOFF SPEED.name: DESIGN TAKEOFF SPEED
DESIGN TAKEOFF SPEED.description: This design constant represents the aircraft ideal takoff speed. It is derived from the takeoff_speed setting in the [REFERENCE SPEEDS] section of the flightmodel.cfg.

FUEL SELECTED TRANSFER MODE.name: FUEL SELECTED TRANSFER MODE
FUEL SELECTED TRANSFER MODE.description:
The method of transfer for the fuel. Each of the available transfer options are explained below:
          
            off - Fuel transfer is switched off.
            auto - Automatically balance the fuel between the Center1 and Center2 tanks to maintain the center of gravity.
            forward - Fuel will be transferred forwards from the Center1 tank to the Center2 tank.
            aft - Fuel will be transferred aftwards from the Center2 tank to the Center1 tank.
            manual - Fuel will be transferred for 1 second from the Center1 tank to the Center2 tank at a rate of 1lbs/s.  
            custom - This requires one or more pumps to have been defined using the fuel_transfer_pump.N parameter in the flight_model.cfg file, as well as their associated electrical circuits.
FUEL SELECTED TRANSFER MODE.units:
Enum:
          
            0 = off
            1 = auto
            2 = forward
            3 = aft
            4 = manual
            5 = custom

FUELSYSTEM TANK LEVEL.name: FUELSYSTEM TANK LEVEL:index

FUELSYSTEM TANK QUANTITY.name: FUELSYSTEM TANK QUANTITY:index

FUELSYSTEM TANK TOTAL QUANTITY.name: FUELSYSTEM TANK TOTAL QUANTITY:index
FUELSYSTEM TANK TOTAL QUANTITY.description: Total quantity of fuel available in the indexed fuel tank, including any unusable fuel. The index is the number of the tank N component as defined by the Tank.N parameter.

FUELSYSTEM TANK WEIGHT.name: FUELSYSTEM TANK WEIGHT:index
FUELSYSTEM TANK WEIGHT.description: Weight of fuel available in the indexed fuel tank. The index is the number of the tank N component as defined by the Tank.N parameter.

FUELSYSTEM TRIGGER STATUS.name: FUELSYSTEM TRIGGER STATUS:index

FUELSYSTEM VALVE OPEN.name: FUELSYSTEM VALVE OPEN:index
FUELSYSTEM VALVE OPEN.description: Whether or not the indexed valve is actually fully opened. The index is the number of the valve N component as defined by the Valve.N parameter.

FUELSYSTEM VALVE SWITCH.name: FUELSYSTEM VALVE SWITCH:index
FUELSYSTEM VALVE SWITCH.description: Whether or not the indexed valve is set to be opened. The index is the number of the valve N component as defined by the Valve.N parameter.

FUEL TANK EXTERNAL1 LEVEL.description: Percent of maximum capacity of the 1st external tank.

FUEL TANK EXTERNAL2 CAPACITY.description: Maximum capacity in volume of the 2nd external tank.

FUEL TANK EXTERNAL2 LEVEL.description: Percent of maximum capacity of the 2nd external tank.

FUEL TANK EXTERNAL2 QUANTITY.name: FUEL TANK EXTERNAL2 QUANTITY
FUEL TANK EXTERNAL2 QUANTITY.description: Current quantity in volume of the 2nd external tank.

FUEL TANK LEFT AUX LEVEL.description: Percent of maximum capacity of the left auxilliary tank.

FUEL TANK LEFT MAIN CAPACITY.description: Maximum capacity in volume of the left main tank.

FUEL TANK LEFT MAIN LEVEL.description: Percent of maximum capacity of the left main tank.

FUEL TANK LEFT MAIN QUANTITY.name: FUEL TANK LEFT MAIN QUANTITY
FUEL TANK LEFT MAIN QUANTITY.description: Current quantity in volume of the left main tank.

FUEL TANK LEFT TIP CAPACITY.name: FUEL TANK LEFT TIP CAPACITY
FUEL TANK LEFT TIP CAPACITY.description: Maximum capacity in volume of the left tip tank.

FUEL TANK LEFT TIP LEVEL.name: FUEL TANK LEFT TIP LEVEL
FUEL TANK LEFT TIP LEVEL.description: Percent of maximum capacity of the left tip tank.

FUEL TANK LEFT TIP QUANTITY.description: Current quantity in volume of the left tip tank.

FUEL TANK RIGHT AUX CAPACITY.name: FUEL TANK RIGHT AUX CAPACITY
FUEL TANK RIGHT AUX CAPACITY.description: Maximum capacity in volume of the right auxilliary tank.

FUEL TANK RIGHT AUX LEVEL.name: FUEL TANK RIGHT AUX LEVEL
FUEL TANK RIGHT AUX LEVEL.description: Percent of maximum capacity of the right auxilliary tank.

FUEL TANK RIGHT AUX QUANTITY.name: FUEL TANK RIGHT AUX QUANTITY
FUEL TANK RIGHT AUX QUANTITY.description: Current quantity in volume of the right auxilliary tank.

FUEL TANK RIGHT MAIN CAPACITY.description: Maximum capacity in volume of the right main tank.

FUEL TANK RIGHT MAIN LEVEL.description: Percent of maximum capacity of the right main tank.

FUEL TANK RIGHT TIP CAPACITY.description: Maximum capacity in volume of the right tip tank.

FUEL TANK RIGHT TIP LEVEL.name: FUEL TANK RIGHT TIP LEVEL
FUEL TANK RIGHT TIP LEVEL.description: Percent of maximum capacity of the right tip tank.

FUEL TANK RIGHT TIP QUANTITY.name: FUEL TANK RIGHT TIP QUANTITY
FUEL TANK RIGHT TIP QUANTITY.description: Current quantity in volume of the right tip tank.

FUEL TANK SELECTOR.name: FUEL TANK SELECTOR:index
FUEL TANK SELECTOR.description: Which tank the indexed selector is set to. The index is the selector to check (from 1 to 4), and the return value will be one of the values listed in the Fuel Tank Selection table.

AMBIENT IN CLOUD.name: AMBIENT IN CLOUD
AMBIENT IN CLOUD.description: True if the aircraft is in a cloud.

CONTRAILS CONDITIONS MET.name: CONTRAILS CONDITIONS MET
CONTRAILS CONDITIONS MET.description: True if the aircraft has met the conditions required to spawn the contrail VFX.

IS USER SIM.name: IS USER SIM
IS USER SIM.description: Is this the user loaded aircraft

ON ANY RUNWAY.name: ON ANY RUNWAY
ON ANY RUNWAY.description: Whether or not the plane is currently on a runway.

PLANE IN PARKING STATE.name: PLANE IN PARKING STATE
PLANE IN PARKING STATE.description: Whether or not the plane is currently parked (true) or not (false).

SURFACE CONDITION.name: SURFACE CONDITION
SURFACE CONDITION.description: The state of the surface directly under the aircraft.

SURFACE INFO VALID.name: SURFACE INFO VALID
SURFACE INFO VALID.description: True indicates that the SURFACE CONDITION return value is meaningful.

STRUCTURAL ICE PCT.name: STRUCTURAL ICE PCT
STRUCTURAL ICE PCT.description: Amount of ice on aircraft structure. 100 is fully iced.

TOW CONNECTION.name: TOW CONNECTION
TOW CONNECTION.description: True if a towline is connected to both tow plane and glider.

WINDSHIELD RAIN EFFECT AVAILABLE.name: WINDSHIELD RAIN EFFECT AVAILABLE
WINDSHIELD RAIN EFFECT AVAILABLE.description: Is visual effect available on this aircraft

ACCELERATION BODY X.name: ACCELERATION BODY X
ACCELERATION BODY X.description: Acceleration relative to aircraft axis, in east/west direction

ACCELERATION BODY Y.name: ACCELERATION BODY Y
ACCELERATION BODY Y.description: Acceleration relative to aircraft axis, in vertical direction

ACCELERATION BODY Z.name: ACCELERATION BODY Z
ACCELERATION BODY Z.description: Acceleration relative to aircraft axis, in north/south direction

ACCELERATION WORLD X.name: ACCELERATION WORLD X
ACCELERATION WORLD X.description: Acceleration relative to earth, in east/west direction

ACCELERATION WORLD Y.name: ACCELERATION WORLD Y
ACCELERATION WORLD Y.description: Acceleration relative to earth, in vertical direction

ACCELERATION WORLD Z.name: ACCELERATION WORLD Z
ACCELERATION WORLD Z.description: Acceleration relative to earth, in north/south direction

SURFACE RELATIVE GROUND SPEED.name: SURFACE RELATIVE GROUND SPEED
SURFACE RELATIVE GROUND SPEED.description: The speed of the aircraft relative to the speed of the first surface directly underneath it. Use this to retrieve, for example, an aircraft's taxiing speed while it is moving on a moving carrier. It also applies to airborne aircraft, for example when a helicopter is successfully hovering above a moving ship, this value should be zero. The returned value will be the same as GROUND VELOCITY if the first surface beneath it is not moving.

GROUND VELOCITY.name: GROUND VELOCITY
GROUND VELOCITY.description: Speed relative to the earths surface

PLANE ALT ABOVE GROUND MINUS CG.name: PLANE ALT ABOVE GROUND MINUS CG
PLANE ALT ABOVE GROUND MINUS CG.description: Altitude above the surface minus CG
PLANE ALT ABOVE GROUND MINUS CG.name_std: PLANE ALT ABOVE GROUND MINUS CG

PLANE BANK DEGREES.name: PLANE BANK DEGREES
PLANE BANK DEGREES.description: Bank angle, although the name mentions degrees the units used are radians

PLANE HEADING DEGREES MAGNETIC.name: PLANE HEADING DEGREES MAGNETIC
PLANE HEADING DEGREES MAGNETIC.description: Heading relative to magnetic north - although the name mentions degrees the units used are radians

PLANE HEADING DEGREES TRUE.name: PLANE HEADING DEGREES TRUE
PLANE HEADING DEGREES TRUE.description: Heading relative to true north - although the name mentions degrees the units used are radians

PLANE LATITUDE.name: PLANE LATITUDE
PLANE LATITUDE.description: Latitude of aircraft, North is positive, South negative

PLANE LONGITUDE.name: PLANE LONGITUDE
PLANE LONGITUDE.description: Longitude of aircraft, East is positive, West negative

PLANE PITCH DEGREES.name: PLANE PITCH DEGREES
PLANE PITCH DEGREES.description: Pitch angle, although the name mentions degrees the units used are radians

PLANE TOUCHDOWN BANK DEGREES.name: PLANE TOUCHDOWN BANK DEGREES
PLANE TOUCHDOWN BANK DEGREES.description: This float represents the bank of the player's plane from the last touchdown. (Not previsouly in FSX)

PLANE TOUCHDOWN HEADING DEGREES MAGNETIC.name: PLANE TOUCHDOWN HEADING DEGREES MAGNETIC
PLANE TOUCHDOWN HEADING DEGREES MAGNETIC.description: This float represents the magnetic heading of the player's plane from the last touchdown. (Not previsouly in FSX)

PLANE TOUCHDOWN HEADING DEGREES TRUE.name: PLANE TOUCHDOWN HEADING DEGREES TRUE
PLANE TOUCHDOWN HEADING DEGREES TRUE.description: This float represents the true heading of the player's plane from the last touchdown. (Not previsouly in FSX)

PLANE TOUCHDOWN LATITUDE.name: PLANE TOUCHDOWN LATITUDE
PLANE TOUCHDOWN LATITUDE.description: This float represents the plane latitude for the last touchdown. (Not previsouly in FSX)

PLANE TOUCHDOWN LONGITUDE.name: PLANE TOUCHDOWN LONGITUDE
PLANE TOUCHDOWN LONGITUDE.description: This float represents the plane longitude for the last touchdown. (Not previsouly in FSX)

PLANE TOUCHDOWN NORMAL VELOCITY.name: PLANE TOUCHDOWN NORMAL VELOCITY
PLANE TOUCHDOWN NORMAL VELOCITY.description: This float represents the player's plane speed according to ground normal from the last touchdown. (Not previsouly in FSX)

PLANE TOUCHDOWN PITCH DEGREES.name: PLANE TOUCHDOWN PITCH DEGREES
PLANE TOUCHDOWN PITCH DEGREES.description: This float represents the pitch of the player's plane from the last touchdown. (Not previsouly in FSX)

ROTATION ACCELERATION BODY X.name: ROTATION ACCELERATION BODY X
ROTATION ACCELERATION BODY X.description: Rotation acceleration relative to aircraft axis

ROTATION ACCELERATION BODY Y.name: ROTATION ACCELERATION BODY Y
ROTATION ACCELERATION BODY Y.description: Rotation acceleration relative to aircraft axis

ROTATION ACCELERATION BODY Z.name: ROTATION ACCELERATION BODY Z
ROTATION ACCELERATION BODY Z.description: Rotation acceleration relative to aircraft axis

SLOPE TO ATC RUNWAY.name: SLOPE TO ATC RUNWAY
SLOPE TO ATC RUNWAY.description: The slope between the plane and the expected landing position of the runway. Returns 0 if no runway is assigned.

VELOCITY BODY X.name: VELOCITY BODY X
VELOCITY BODY X.description: True lateral speed, relative to aircraft axis

VELOCITY BODY Y.name: VELOCITY BODY Y
VELOCITY BODY Y.description: True vertical speed, relative to aircraft axis

VELOCITY BODY Z.name: VELOCITY BODY Z
VELOCITY BODY Z.description: True longitudinal speed, relative to aircraft axis

VERTICAL SPEED.name: VERTICAL SPEED
VERTICAL SPEED.description: The current indicated vertical speed for the aircraft.

EYEPOINT POSITION.name: EYEPOINT POSITION
EYEPOINT POSITION.description: The eyepoint position relative to the reference datum position for the aircraft.

STRUC AIRSPEED HOLD PID CONSTS.name: STRUC AIRSPEED HOLD PID CONSTS
STRUC AIRSPEED HOLD PID CONSTS.description: Returns the various airspeed PID constants. This is generally only used for AI controlled aircraft and boats, although it may be useful when working with RTCs and the user aircraft.

STRUC HEADING HOLD PID CONSTS.name: STRUC HEADING HOLD PID CONSTS
STRUC HEADING HOLD PID CONSTS.description: Returns the various airspeed PID constants. This is generally only used for AI controlled aircraft and boats, although it may be useful when working with RTCs and the user aircraft.

STRUCT ENGINE POSITION.name: STRUCT ENGINE POSITION
STRUCT ENGINE POSITION.description: The engine position relative to the reference datum position for the aircraft.

STRUCT EYEPOINT DYNAMIC ANGLE.name: STRUCT EYEPOINT DYNAMIC ANGLE
STRUCT EYEPOINT DYNAMIC ANGLE.description: The angle of the eyepoint view. Zero, zero, zero is straight ahead.

STRUCT EYEPOINT DYNAMIC OFFSET.name: STRUCT EYEPOINT DYNAMIC OFFSET
STRUCT EYEPOINT DYNAMIC OFFSET.description: A variable offset away from the EYEPOINT POSITION

STRUCT LATLONALT.name: STRUCT LATLONALT
STRUCT LATLONALT.description: Returns the latitude, longitude and altitude of the user aircraft.

STRUCT LATLONALTPBH.name: STRUCT LATLONALTPBH
STRUCT LATLONALTPBH.description: Returns the pitch, bank and heading of the user aircraft.

AIRCRAFT WIND X.name: AIRCRAFT WIND X
AIRCRAFT WIND X.description: Wind component in aircraft lateral axis

AIRCRAFT WIND Y.name: AIRCRAFT WIND Y
AIRCRAFT WIND Y.description: Wind component in aircraft vertical axis

AIRCRAFT WIND Z.name: AIRCRAFT WIND Z
AIRCRAFT WIND Z.description: Wind component in aircraft longitudinal axis

AIRSPEED SELECT INDICATED OR TRUE.name: AIRSPEED SELECT INDICATED OR TRUE
AIRSPEED SELECT INDICATED OR TRUE.description: The airspeed, whether true or indicated airspeed has been selected.

AIRSPEED TRUE RAW.name: AIRSPEED TRUE RAW
AIRSPEED TRUE RAW.description: Equivalent to AIRSPEED TRUE, but does not account for wind when used to Set Airspeed value

TOTAL VELOCITY.name: TOTAL VELOCITY
TOTAL VELOCITY.description: Velocity regardless of direction. For example, if a helicopter is ascending vertically at 100 fps, getting this variable will return 100.

WINDSHIELD WIND VELOCITY.name: WINDSHIELD WIND VELOCITY
WINDSHIELD WIND VELOCITY.description: Longitudinal speed of wind on the windshield

STANDARD ATM TEMPERATURE.name: STANDARD ATM TEMPERATURE
STANDARD ATM TEMPERATURE.description: Outside temperature on the standard ATM scale

TOTAL AIR TEMPERATURE.name: TOTAL AIR TEMPERATURE
TOTAL AIR TEMPERATURE.description: Total air temperature is the air temperature at the front of the aircraft where the ram pressure from the speed of the aircraft is taken into account.

IS ATTACHED TO SLING.name: IS ATTACHED TO SLING
IS ATTACHED TO SLING.description: Set to true if this object is attached to a sling.

NUM SLING CABLES.name: NUM SLING CABLES
NUM SLING CABLES.description: The number of sling cables (not hoists) that are configured for the aircraft. Refer to the document Notes on Aircraft Systems.

SLING ACTIVE PAYLOAD STATION.name: SLING ACTIVE PAYLOAD STATION
SLING ACTIVE PAYLOAD STATION.description: The payload station (identified by the parameter) where objects will be placed from the sling (identified by the index).

SLING CABLE BROKEN.name: SLING CABLE BROKEN
SLING CABLE BROKEN.description: True if the cable is broken.

SLING CABLE EXTENDED LENGTH.name: SLING CABLE EXTENDED LENGTH
SLING CABLE EXTENDED LENGTH.description: The length of the cable extending from the aircraft.

SLING HOIST PERCENT DEPLOYED.name: SLING HOIST PERCENT DEPLOYED
SLING HOIST PERCENT DEPLOYED.description: The percentage of the full length of the sling cable deployed.

SLING HOIST SWITCH.name: SLING HOIST SWITCH
SLING HOIST SWITCH.description: True if the hoist is enabled.

SLING HOOK IN PICKUP MODE.name: SLING HOOK IN PICKUP MODE
SLING HOOK IN PICKUP MODE.description: A Boolean for whether or not the hook is in pickup mode, so capable of picking up another object.

SLING OBJECT ATTACHED.name: SLING OBJECT ATTACHED
SLING OBJECT ATTACHED.description: If units are set as boolean, returns True if a sling object is attached. If units are set as a string, returns the container title of the object.There can be multiple sling positions, indexed from 1. The sling positions are set in the Aircraft Configuration File.

ADF LATLONALT.name: ADF LATLONALT:index
ADF LATLONALT.description: Returns the latitude, longitude and altitude of the station the radio equipment is currently tuned to, or zeros if the radio is not tuned to any ADF station. Index of 1 or 2 for ADF 1 and ADF 2.

ADF RADIAL MAG.name: ADF RADIAL MAG
ADF RADIAL MAG.description: Returns the magnetic bearing to the currently tuned ADF transmitter.

ADF SOUND.name: ADF SOUND
ADF SOUND.description: ADF audio flag. Index of 0 or 1.

ADF STANDBY AVAILABLE.name: ADF STANDBY AVAILABLE
ADF STANDBY AVAILABLE.description: True if ADF Standby is available

ADF VOLUME.name: ADF VOLUME
ADF VOLUME.description: Returns the volume of the ADF

ATC AIRLINE.name: ATC AIRLINE
ATC AIRLINE.description: The name of the Airline used by ATC, as a string with a maximum length of 50 characters.

ATC AIRPORT IS TOWERED.name: ATC AIRPORT IS TOWERED
ATC AIRPORT IS TOWERED.description: If the airport is controlled, this boolean is true

ATC CLEARED IFR.name: ATC CLEARED IFR
ATC CLEARED IFR.description: Returns whether or not the user has filed an IFR flightplan that has been cleared by the sim ATC

ATC CLEARED LANDING.name: ATC CLEARED LANDING
ATC CLEARED LANDING.description: Whether the ATC has cleared the plane for landing.

ATC CLEARED TAKEOFF.name: ATC CLEARED TAKEOFF
ATC CLEARED TAKEOFF.description: Whether the ATC has cleared the plane for takeoff.

ATC CLEARED TAXI.name: ATC CLEARED TAXI
ATC CLEARED TAXI.description: Whether the ATC has cleared the plane for taxi.

ATC CURRENT WAYPOINT ALTITUDE.name: ATC CURRENT WAYPOINT ALTITUDE
ATC CURRENT WAYPOINT ALTITUDE.description: Returns the target altitude for the current ATC flightplan waypoint.

ATC FLIGHT NUMBER.name: ATC FLIGHT NUMBER
ATC FLIGHT NUMBER.description: Flight Number used by ATC, as a string with a maximum number of 6 characters.

ATC FLIGHTPLAN DIFF ALT.name: ATC FLIGHTPLAN DIFF ALT
ATC FLIGHTPLAN DIFF ALT.description: Altitude between the position of the aircraft and his closest waypoints in the flightplan

ATC FLIGHTPLAN DIFF DISTANCE.name: ATC FLIGHTPLAN DIFF DISTANCE
ATC FLIGHTPLAN DIFF DISTANCE.description: Returns the lateral distance the user's plane is from the ATC flight plan track.

ATC FLIGHTPLAN DIFF HEADING.name: ATC FLIGHTPLAN DIFF HEADING
ATC FLIGHTPLAN DIFF HEADING.description: Heading between the position of the aircraft and his closest waypoints in the flightplan

ATC HEAVY.name: ATC HEAVY
ATC HEAVY.description: Is this aircraft recognized by ATC as heavy

ATC ID.name: ATC ID
ATC ID.description: ID used by ATC, as a string with a maximum number of 10 characters.

ATC IFR FP TO REQUEST.name: ATC IFR FP TO REQUEST
ATC IFR FP TO REQUEST.description: Returns true if the user has a valid IFR flight plan they can as for clearance for with ATC at the airport they are currently at.

ATC MODEL.name: ATC MODEL
ATC MODEL.description: Model used by ATC, as a string with a maximum number of 10 characters.

ATC ON PARKING SPOT.name: ATC ON PARKING SPOT
ATC ON PARKING SPOT.description: Is ATC aircraft on parking spot

ATC PREVIOUS WAYPOINT ALTITUDE.name: ATC PREVIOUS WAYPOINT ALTITUDE
ATC PREVIOUS WAYPOINT ALTITUDE.description: Returns the target altitude for the previous ATC flightplan waypoint.

ATC RUNWAY AIRPORT NAME.name: ATC RUNWAY AIRPORT NAME
ATC RUNWAY AIRPORT NAME.description: The name of the airport of the runway assigned by the ATC. Returns "" if no runway is assigned.

ATC RUNWAY DISTANCE.name: ATC RUNWAY DISTANCE
ATC RUNWAY DISTANCE.description: This float represents the distance between the player's plane and the center of the runway selected by the ATC.

ATC RUNWAY END DISTANCE.name: ATC RUNWAY END DISTANCE
ATC RUNWAY END DISTANCE.description: This is a float corresponding to the horizontal distance between the player's plane and the end of the runway selected by the ATC.

ATC RUNWAY HEADING DEGREES TRUE.name: ATC RUNWAY HEADING DEGREES TRUE
ATC RUNWAY HEADING DEGREES TRUE.description: This float represents the true heading of the runway selected by the ATC.

ATC RUNWAY LENGTH.name: ATC RUNWAY LENGTH
ATC RUNWAY LENGTH.description: The length of the runway assigned by the ATC. Returns -1 if no runway is assigned.

ATC RUNWAY RELATIVE POSITION X.name: ATC RUNWAY RELATIVE POSITION X
ATC RUNWAY RELATIVE POSITION X.description: This is a float corresponding to the player's main gear relative X (transverse) position on the runway selected by the ATC.

ATC RUNWAY RELATIVE POSITION Y.name: ATC RUNWAY RELATIVE POSITION Y
ATC RUNWAY RELATIVE POSITION Y.description: This is a float corresponding to the player's main gear relative Y (height) position on the runway selected by the ATC.

ATC RUNWAY RELATIVE POSITION Z.name: ATC RUNWAY RELATIVE POSITION Z
ATC RUNWAY RELATIVE POSITION Z.description: This is a float corresponding to the player's main gear relative Z (longitudinal) position on the runway selected by the ATC.

ATC RUNWAY SELECTED.name: ATC RUNWAY SELECTED
ATC RUNWAY SELECTED.description: This is a boolean corresponding to whether or not the ATC has pre-selected a runway for the player's plane. If this is false, every other ATC_RUNWAY SimVar will return default values.

ATC RUNWAY START DISTANCE.name: ATC RUNWAY START DISTANCE
ATC RUNWAY START DISTANCE.description: This is a float corresponding to the horizontal distance between the player's plane and the start of the runway selected by the ATC.

ATC RUNWAY TDPOINT RELATIVE POSITION X.name: ATC RUNWAY TDPOINT RELATIVE POSITION X
ATC RUNWAY TDPOINT RELATIVE POSITION X.description: This float represents the player's main gear relative X (transverse) position accorindg to the aiming point of the runway selected by the ATC.
ATC RUNWAY TDPOINT RELATIVE POSITION X.name_std: ATC RUNWAY TDPOINT RELATIVE POSITION X

ATC RUNWAY TDPOINT RELATIVE POSITION Y.name: ATC RUNWAY TDPOINT RELATIVE POSITION Y
ATC RUNWAY TDPOINT RELATIVE POSITION Y.description: This float represents the player's main gear relative Y (height) position accorindg to the aiming point of the runway selected by the ATC.
ATC RUNWAY TDPOINT RELATIVE POSITION Y.name_std: ATC RUNWAY TDPOINT RELATIVE POSITION Y

ATC RUNWAY TDPOINT RELATIVE POSITION Z.name: ATC RUNWAY TDPOINT RELATIVE POSITION Z
ATC RUNWAY TDPOINT RELATIVE POSITION Z.description: This float represents the player's main relative Z (longitudinal) position accorindg to the aiming point of the runway selected by the ATC.
ATC RUNWAY TDPOINT RELATIVE POSITION Z.name_std: ATC RUNWAY TDPOINT RELATIVE POSITION Z

ATC RUNWAY WIDTH.name: ATC RUNWAY WIDTH
ATC RUNWAY WIDTH.description: The width of the runway assigned by the ATC. Returns -1 if no runway is assigned.

GPS FLIGHTPLAN TOTAL DISTANCE.description: This is the complete flightplan length from start to end. Essentially the cumulative length of all the flight plan legs added together.

GPS OBS VALUE.description: This is the currently selected OBS course in degrees, from 0 to 360.

GPS OVERRIDDEN.description: When it is active, all sim GPS system updates are suspended. This must be set to TRUE to be able to correctly set to any other GPS SimVar.

GPS VERTICAL ANGLE ERROR.description: Vertical error in degrees from GlidePath

HSI BEARING.name: HSI BEARING
HSI BEARING.description: If the GPS_DRIVES_NAV1 variable is true and the HSI BEARING VALID variable is true, this variable contains the HSI needle bearing. If the GPS DRIVES NAV1 variable is false and the HSI BEARING VALID variable is true, this variable contains the ADF1 frequency.

HSI BEARING VALID.description: This will return true if the HSI BEARING variable contains valid data.

HSI STATION IDENT.name: HSI STATION IDENT
HSI STATION IDENT.description: Returns the ident of the the next GPS waypoint, if GPS_DRIVES_NAV1 is true. If GPS DRIVES NAV1 is false, it returns the identity of the station that is tuned on nav radio 1.

INNER MARKER LATLONALT.name: INNER MARKER LATLONALT
INNER MARKER LATLONALT.description: Returns the latitude, longitude and altitude of the inner marker of an approach to a runway, if the aircraft is within the required proximity, otherwise it will return zeros.

OUTER MARKER LATLONALT.name: OUTER MARKER LATLONALT

NAV GLIDE SLOPE LENGTH.description: The distance between the plane and the Glide beacon.

NAV GSI.description: Glideslope needle deflection (+/- 119). Note that this provides only 8 bit precision, whereas NAV GLIDE SLOPE ERROR provides 32 bit floating point precision.

NAV HAS CLOSE DME.description: Flag if found a close station with a DME

NAV HAS TACAN.description: Flag if Nav has a Tacan.

NAV STANDBY FREQUENCY.description: Nav standby frequency. Index is 1 or 2.

NAV VOLUME.description: The volume of the Nav radio

NAV VOR LATLONALT.description: Returns the VOR station latitude, longitude and altitude.

TACAN VOLUME.description: The volume value of the indexed Tacan receiver on the aircraft.

FIRE BOTTLE SWITCH.description: True if the fire bottle switch is on.

GPWS SYSTEM ACTIVE.description: True if the Ground Proximity Warning System is active

INDICATED ALTITUDE CALIBRATED.description: Indicated altitude with the altimeter calibrated to current sea level pressure.

INDICATED ALTITUDE EX1.description: Similar to INDICATED_ALTITUDE but doesn't affect actual plane position when setting this variable.

INTERCOM SYSTEM ACTIVE.description: Whether or not the intercom system is active.

IS ATTITUDE FREEZE ON.description: True if the attitude (pitch, bank and heading) of the aircraft is frozen.

True if the lat/lon of the aircraft (either user or AI controlled) is frozen. If this variable returns true, it means that the latitude and longitude of the aircraft are not being controlled by ESP, so enabling, for example, a SimConnect client to control the position of the aircraft.           Also refer to the range of KEY_FREEZE..... Event IDs.

KOHLSMAN SETTING HG.name: KOHLSMAN SETTING HG:index
KOHLSMAN SETTING HG.description:
The value for the given altimeter index in inches of mercury.
          IMPORTANT! In the system.cfg file, altimeters are indexed from 0, but the SimVar indexes from 1. So, altimeter 0 in that file is accessed using KOHLSMAN SETTING HG:1, 1 by KOHLSMAN SETTING HG:2, etc...

KOHLSMAN SETTING MB.name: KOHLSMAN SETTING MB:index
KOHLSMAN SETTING MB.description:
The value for the given altimeter index in millibars.
          IMPORTANT! In the system.cfg file, altimeters are indexed from 0, but the SimVar indexes from 1. So, altimeter 0 in that file is accessed using KOHLSMAN SETTING MB:1, 1 by KOHLSMAN SETTING MB:2, etc...

KOHLSMAN SETTING STD.name: KOHLSMAN SETTING STD:index
KOHLSMAN SETTING STD.description:
True if the indexed altimeter is in "Standard" mode, or false otherwise.
          IMPORTANT! In the system.cfg file, altimeters are indexed from 0, but the SimVar indexes from 1. So, altimeter 0 in that file is accessed using KOHLSMAN SETTING STD:1, 1 by KOHLSMAN SETTING STD:2, etc...

MANUAL FUEL PUMP HANDLE.name: MANUAL FUEL PUMP HANDLE

PANEL ANTI ICE SWITCH.description: True if panel anti-ice switch is on

PITOT ICE PCT.name: PITOT ICE PCT

PRESSURIZATION CABIN ALTITUDE.name: PRESSURIZATION CABIN ALTITUDE

PRESSURIZATION CABIN ALTITUDE GOAL.description: The set altitude of the cabin pressurization.

PRESSURIZATION CABIN ALTITUDE RATE.description: The rate at which cabin pressurization changes.

PRESSURIZATION DUMP SWITCH.name: PRESSURIZATION DUMP SWITCH
PRESSURIZATION DUMP SWITCH.description: True if the cabin pressurization dump switch is on.

PRESSURIZATION PRESSURE DIFFERENTIAL.name: PRESSURIZATION PRESSURE DIFFERENTIAL

RAD INS SWITCH.name: RAD INS SWITCH

WATER BALLAST VALVE.name: WATER BALLAST VALVE
WATER BALLAST VALVE.description: True if water ballast valve is available

WINDSHIELD DEICE SWITCH.name: WINDSHIELD DEICE SWITCH

WISKEY COMPASS INDICATION DEGREES.name: WISKEY COMPASS INDICATION DEGREES

CAMERA GAMEPLAY PITCH YAW.name: CAMERA GAMEPLAY PITCH YAW:index
CAMERA GAMEPLAY PITCH YAW.description: Returns either the pitch (index 0) or the yaw (index 1) of the current gameplay camera.

CAMERA REQUEST ACTION.name: CAMERA REQUEST ACTION
CAMERA REQUEST ACTION.description: This can be used to have the currently active camera perform a predefined action. Currently only 1 action is supported, but more may be added over time.

CAMERA STATE.name: CAMERA STATE
CAMERA STATE.description:
This can be used to get or set the camera "state", which will be one of the listed enum values.
          Note that not ALL possible enum values are shown, since some values are internal only, and some values will do nothing, but have been reserved for future expansion of the camera system. 
          Also note that the value "8" is a special case, generally used only when working with in-sim panels and is used to go to the showcase cameras, defaulting to the last selected camera within this section (Drone, Fixed or Environment).
CAMERA STATE.units:
Enum:
          
            2 = Cockpit
            3 = External/Chase
            4 = Drone
            5 = Fixed on Plane
            6 = Environment
            8 = Showcase
            9 = Drone Plane
            11 = World Map
            12 = Hanger RTC
            13 = Menu RTC
            14 = In-Sim RTC
            18 = Hanger
            21 = Ground
            22 = Follow Air Traffic

CAMERA SUBSTATE.name: CAMERA SUBSTATE
CAMERA SUBSTATE.description: This variable can be used to get or set the camera "sub-state". The options here are generally only required when working with the in-sim panel UI. Note that the "locked" and "unlocked" state will be changed automatically if the following SimVars have their values changed: COCKPIT_CAMERA_HEADLOOK, CHASE_CAMERA_HEADLOOK.
CAMERA SUBSTATE.units:
Enum:
          
            1 = Locked (Fixed look or chase lock -
                
                The camera is locked in position)
            2 = Unlocked (Head look or Chase
                
                normal - The camera is "attached" to
                
                the mouse)
            3 = Quickview (the camera is
                
                currently using a Quickview)
            4 = Smart (The camera has Smart
                
                camera active)
            5 = Instrument (The camera is
                
                focused on an instruments panel)

CAMERA VIEW TYPE AND INDEX.name: CAMERA VIEW TYPE AND INDEX:index
CAMERA VIEW TYPE AND INDEX.description:
With this you can get or set both the type of view for the current camera, as well as the option index, which will be between 0 and the maximum index value (as retrieved using the CAMERA VIEW TYPE AND INDEX MAX SimVar). Supplying an index of 0 to the SimVar will get/set the type (from the selection of enum values listed), and using an index of 1 will get/set the option index, which is an integer value.
           
          Please see the Notes On View Types And Indices section below for more information.
CAMERA VIEW TYPE AND INDEX.units:
Enum (index = 0):
          
            0 = Unknown/default
            (External / Chase and Showcase /
                
                Drone / Fixed / Environment states)
            1 = Pilot View
            (Cockpit State)
            2 = Instruments
            (Cockpit State)
            3 = Quickview
            (Cockpit State)
            4 = Quickview External
            (External State)
            5 = View
            (Showcase / Drone / Fixed /
                
                Environment states)
          
          or
          Number (index = 1)

CAMERA VIEW TYPE AND INDEX MAX.name: CAMERA VIEW TYPE AND INDEX MAX:index
CAMERA VIEW TYPE AND INDEX MAX.description:
This variable can get the number of option indices related to a specific camera view type. The index value supplied to the SimVar should be one of the camera view type Enum values (see CAMERA VIEW TYPE AND INDEX), and the SimVar will return the number of options available for that camera type (counting from 1, so - for example - if the camera view type is "Quickview" and has 8 quickview settings, then CAMERA VIEW TYPE AND INDEX MAX:4 will return 8). Note that this value can be set after a flight has started, but it will have no effect since the number of camera options is initilaised once only and not updated (and the simulation may overwrite the value again even after setting it).
           
          Please see the Notes On View Types And Indices section below for more information.
CAMERA VIEW TYPE AND INDEX MAX.name_std: CAMERA VIEW TYPE AND INDEX MAX

GAMEPLAY CAMERA FOCUS.name: GAMEPLAY CAMERA FOCUS
GAMEPLAY CAMERA FOCUS.description:
This gets/sets the focus for the camera zoom, which can be either manual, or auto. The setting affects both the Cockpit and the External (Chase) cameras.
          The following SimVars can be used to get/set the level of zoom: COCKPIT_CAMERA_ZOOM or CHASE_CAMERA_ZOOM.

CHASE CAMERA HEADLOOK.name: CHASE CAMERA HEADLOOK
CHASE CAMERA HEADLOOK.description: This is used to get/set the look state of the chase (external) camera. Note that this value will also affect the CAMERA_SUBSTATE value, when the CAMERA_STATE is set to 3 (External/Chase).

CHASE CAMERA MOMENTUM.name: CHASE CAMERA MOMENTUM
CHASE CAMERA MOMENTUM.description: Sets/gets the momentum modifier of the chase (external) camera, which is controls how fast/slow the camera will stop moving when no longer being moved by the user. Default is 50%.

CHASE CAMERA SPEED.name: CHASE CAMERA SPEED
CHASE CAMERA SPEED.description: Sets/gets the translation speed modifier of the chase (external) camara, as a percentage. Default is 50%.

CHASE CAMERA ZOOM.name: CHASE CAMERA ZOOM
CHASE CAMERA ZOOM.description: Sets/gets the zoom/FOV modifier for the chase (external) camera. Note that when setting this value, it will affect the camera regardless of whether the GAMEPLAY_CAMERA_FOCUS is set to manual or automatic. Default is 50%.

CHASE CAMERA ZOOM SPEED.name: CHASE CAMERA ZOOM SPEED
CHASE CAMERA ZOOM SPEED.description: Sets/gets the speed modifier for when the zoom/FOV chase (external) camera changes zoom/FOV levels. Default is 50%.

CAMERA ACTION COCKPIT VIEW RESET.name: CAMERA ACTION COCKPIT VIEW RESET
CAMERA ACTION COCKPIT VIEW RESET.description: This can be used to reset the cockpit camera when the CAMERA_STATE is set to 2 (Cockpit). Essentially the same as the user pressing the default reset keys CTRL + Space.

CAMERA ACTION COCKPIT VIEW SAVE.name: CAMERA ACTION COCKPIT VIEW SAVE:index
CAMERA ACTION COCKPIT VIEW SAVE.description: This can be used to save a cockpit camera when the CAMERA_STATE is set to 2 (Cockpit). The index value given is the save "slot" that will be used, from 0 to 9. Essentially this is the same as the user pressing the default save keys CTRL + Alt + 0-9.

COCKPIT CAMERA HEADLOOK.name: COCKPIT CAMERA HEADLOOK
COCKPIT CAMERA HEADLOOK.description: This is used to get/set the look state of the cockpit camera. Note that this value will also affect the CAMERA_SUBSTATE value, when the CAMERA_STATE is set to 2 (Cockpit).

COCKPIT CAMERA HEIGHT.name: COCKPIT CAMERA HEIGHT
COCKPIT CAMERA HEIGHT.description: This can be used to get/set the cockpit camera height modifier expressed as a percentage. Default is 50%.

COCKPIT CAMERA INSTRUMENT AUTOSELECT.name: COCKPIT CAMERA INSTRUMENT AUTOSELECT
COCKPIT CAMERA INSTRUMENT AUTOSELECT.description: This can be used to get or set the autoselect option for the cockpit camera when viewing the instruments (ie: the CAMERA_SUBSTATE is 5). When enabled the camera will move automatically if the player mouse reaches the edge of the screen and there are instrument panels available on that side.

COCKPIT CAMERA MOMENTUM.name: COCKPIT CAMERA MOMENTUM
COCKPIT CAMERA MOMENTUM.description: Sets/gets the momentum modifier of the cockpit camera, which is controls how fast/slow the camera will stop moving when no longer being moved by the user. Default is 50%.

COCKPIT CAMERA SIDE.name: COCKPIT CAMERA SIDE
COCKPIT CAMERA SIDE.description: Not currently used in the simulation.

COCKPIT CAMERA SPEED.name: COCKPIT CAMERA SPEED
COCKPIT CAMERA SPEED.description: Sets/gets the translation speed modifier of the cockpit camara, as a percentage. Default is 50%.

COCKPIT CAMERA UPPER POSITION.name: COCKPIT CAMERA UPPER POSITION
COCKPIT CAMERA UPPER POSITION.description: Sets/gets the current "upper position" cockpit camera toggle. When 1 (TRUE), the camera is is in the upper position, and when 0 (FALSE) it is in the default position.

COCKPIT CAMERA ZOOM.name: COCKPIT CAMERA ZOOM
COCKPIT CAMERA ZOOM.description: Sets/gets the zoom/FOV modifier for the cockpit camera. Note that when setting this value, it will affect the camera regardless of whether the GAMEPLAY_CAMERA_FOCUS is set to manual or automatic. Default is 50%.

COCKPIT CAMERA ZOOM SPEED.name: COCKPIT CAMERA ZOOM SPEED
COCKPIT CAMERA ZOOM SPEED.description: Sets/gets the speed modifier for when the zoom/FOV cockpit camera changes zoom/FOV levels. Default is 50%.

DRONE CAMERA FOCUS.name: DRONE CAMERA FOCUS
DRONE CAMERA FOCUS.description: Sets/gets the focus modifier for the drone camera. Default is 50%, and a lower value will set the drone focus to things in the foreground and a higher level will set the drone focus to things in the background. Note that this is only taken into account when the DRONE_CAMERA_FOCUS_MODE is set to 3 (manual).

DRONE CAMERA FOCUS MODE.name: DRONE CAMERA FOCUS MODE
DRONE CAMERA FOCUS MODE.description: Sets/gets the current drone focus mode. When set to 3 (manual), the focus position will be based on the DRONE_CAMERA_FOCUS value.

DRONE CAMERA FOLLOW.name: DRONE CAMERA FOLLOW
DRONE CAMERA FOLLOW.description: Sets/gets the whether the drone camera is in follow mode or not.

DRONE CAMERA FOV.name: DRONE CAMERA FOV
DRONE CAMERA FOV.description: Sets/gets the zoom/FOV modifier for the drone camera. Default is 50%.

DRONE CAMERA LOCKED.name: DRONE CAMERA LOCKED
DRONE CAMERA LOCKED.description: Sets/gets the whether the drone camera is locked or not.

DRONE CAMERA SPEED ROTATION.name: DRONE CAMERA SPEED ROTATION
DRONE CAMERA SPEED ROTATION.description: Sets/gets the rotation speed modifier of the drone camara, as a percentage. Default is 50%.

DRONE CAMERA SPEED TRAVELLING.name: DRONE CAMERA SPEED TRAVELLING
DRONE CAMERA SPEED TRAVELLING.description: Sets/gets the translation speed modifier of the drone camara, as a percentage. Default is 50%.

SMART CAMERA ACTIVE.name: SMART CAMERA ACTIVE
SMART CAMERA ACTIVE.description: Sets/gets the whether the smart camera is active or not.

SMART CAMERA INFO.name: SMART CAMERA INFO:index
SMART CAMERA INFO.description:
Gets information on the smartcam system. The index sets what kind of information will be returned (or set):
          
            0 = Gets the number of smartcam targets in the smart camera list
            1 = Gets or sets the index of the currently selected smartcam target, counting from 0 (so index 0 is the first target in the list).

SMART CAMERA LIST.name: SMART CAMERA LIST:index
SMART CAMERA LIST.description: Retrieves the type of target for the indexed position in the smartcam list, counting from 0 (so index 0 is the first target in the list).

Enum:
          
            0 = unknown POI
            1 = Follow POI
            2 = User POI
            3 = General POI
            4 = End OF Runway
            5 = Landing Runway
            6 = Flightpath
            7 = Object Interaction
            8 = Multiplayer OOI
            9 = Active Runway
            10 = Waypoint
            11 = Airport OOI
            12 = Flight Assistant Destination

SMART CAMERA LIST DESCRIPTION.name: SMART CAMERA LIST DESCRIPTION:index
SMART CAMERA LIST DESCRIPTION.description: This returns a localised string that represents the smartcam target specified by the given index. Indices count from 0 so index 0 is the first target in the list.

BAGGAGELOADER PIVOT Z.description: Only for BaggageLoader SimObjects. Z coordinate of the pivot of its ramp.

FUELTRUCK HOSE END POSX.description: Only for FuelTruck SimObjects. X coordinate of the end of its hose, when fully deployed.

FUELTRUCK HOSE END POSZ.name: FUELTRUCK HOSE END POSZ
