TURBINE_IGNITION_SWITCH_TOGGLE.name: TURBINE_IGNITION_SWITCH_TOGGLE
TURBINE_IGNITION_SWITCH_TOGGLE.description: Turn the turbine ignition switch on or off.

AILERON_CENTER.name: AILERON_CENTER
AILERON_CENTER.description:
Centers aileron position
          Not currently supported in the simulation.

AILERON_LEFT.name: AILERON_LEFT
AILERON_LEFT.description:
Increments aileron left
          Not currently supported in the simulation.

AILERON_RIGHT.name: AILERON_RIGHT
AILERON_RIGHT.description:
Increments ailerons right
          Not currently supported in the simulation.

AXIS_AILERONS_SET.name: AXIS_AILERONS_SET
AXIS_AILERONS_SET.multiplayer:
Shared Cockpit
          (Pilot only, and not transmitted to Co-pilot)

AXIS_ELEVATOR_SET.name: AXIS_ELEVATOR_SET
AXIS_ELEVATOR_SET.multiplayer:
Shared Cockpit
          (Pilot only, and not transmitted to Co-pilot)

ELEV_DOWN.name: ELEV_DOWN
ELEV_DOWN.description:
Increments elevator down
          Not currently supported in the simulation.

ELEVATOR_UP.name: ELEVATOR_UP
ELEVATOR_UP.description:
Increments elevator up
          Not currently supported in the simulation.

AXIS_FLAPS_SET.name: AXIS_FLAPS_SET
AXIS_FLAPS_SET.description: Sets flap handle to closest increment (-16383 - +16383)

FLAPS_1.name: FLAPS_1
FLAPS_1.description: Sets flap handle to first extension position

FLAPS_2.name: FLAPS_2
FLAPS_2.description: Sets flap handle to second extension position

FLAPS_3.name: FLAPS_3
FLAPS_3.description: Sets flap handle to third extension position

FLAPS_4.name: FLAPS_4
FLAPS_4.description: Sets flap handle to fourth extension position

FLAPS_DOWN.name: FLAPS_DOWN
FLAPS_DOWN.description: Sets flap handle to full extension position

FLAPS_SET.name: FLAPS_SET
FLAPS_SET.description: Sets flap handle to closest increment (0 to 16383)

FLAPS_UP.name: FLAPS_UP
FLAPS_UP.description: Sets flap handle to full retract position

AUTORUDDER_TOGGLE.name: AUTORUDDER_TOGGLE
AUTORUDDER_TOGGLE.description: Turn the automatic rudder control feature on or off.

AXIS_RUDDER_SET.name: AXIS_RUDDER_SET
AXIS_RUDDER_SET.multiplayer:
Shared Cockpit
          (Pilot only, and not transmitted to Co-pilot)

SLEW_HEADING_MINUS.name: SLEW_HEADING_MINUS
SLEW_HEADING_MINUS.description: Increase slew heading to the left

SLEW_HEADING_PLUS.name: SLEW_HEADING_PLUS
SLEW_HEADING_PLUS.description: Increase slew heading to the right

SLEW_RESET.name: SLEW_RESET
SLEW_RESET.description: Stop slew and reset pitch, bank, and heading all to zero.

SPOILERS_OFF.name: SPOILERS_OFF
SPOILERS_OFF.description: Sets spoiler handle to full retract position

SPOILERS_ON.name: SPOILERS_ON
SPOILERS_ON.description: Sets spoiler handle to full extend position

ATTITUDE_BARS_POSITION_DOWN.name: ATTITUDE_BARS_POSITION_DOWN
ATTITUDE_BARS_POSITION_DOWN.description: Decrements attitude indicator pitch reference bars

ATTITUDE_BARS_POSITION_UP.name: ATTITUDE_BARS_POSITION_UP
ATTITUDE_BARS_POSITION_UP.description: Increments attitude indicator pitch reference bars

BAROMETRIC.name: BAROMETRIC
BAROMETRIC.description: Syncs altimeter setting to sea level pressure, or 29.92 if above 18000 feet

GAUGE_KEYSTROKE.name: GAUGE_KEYSTROKE
GAUGE_KEYSTROKE.description: Enables a keystroke to be sent to a gauge that is in focus. The keystrokes can only be in the range 0 to 9, A to Z, and the four keys: plus, minus, comma and period. This is typically used to allow some keyboard entry to a complex device such as a GPS to enter such things as ICAO codes using the keyboard, rather than turning dials.

HEADING_GYRO_SET.name: HEADING_GYRO_SET
HEADING_GYRO_SET.description: Sets heading indicator to 0 drift error.

RESET_G_FORCE_INDICATOR.name: RESET_G_FORCE_INDICATOR
RESET_G_FORCE_INDICATOR.description: Resets max/min indicated G force to 1.0.

RESET_MAX_RPM_INDICATOR.name: RESET_MAX_RPM_INDICATOR
RESET_MAX_RPM_INDICATOR.description: Reset max indicated engine rpm to 0.

ATTITUDE_CAGE_BUTTON.name: ATTITUDE_CAGE_BUTTON
ATTITUDE_CAGE_BUTTON.description: Cages attitude indicator at 0 pitch and bank

TOGGLE_TURN_INDICATOR_SWITCH.name: TOGGLE_TURN_INDICATOR_SWITCH
TOGGLE_TURN_INDICATOR_SWITCH.description: Turn the turn indicator on or off.

TOGGLE_VARIOMETER_SWITCH.name: TOGGLE_VARIOMETER_SWITCH
TOGGLE_VARIOMETER_SWITCH.description: Turn the variometer on or off.

TRUE_AIRSPEED_CAL_DEC.name: TRUE_AIRSPEED_CAL_DEC
TRUE_AIRSPEED_CAL_DEC.description: Decrements airspeed indicators true airspeed reference card

TRUE_AIRSPEED_CAL_INC.name: TRUE_AIRSPEED_CAL_INC
TRUE_AIRSPEED_CAL_INC.description: Increments airspeed indicators true airspeed reference card

TRUE_AIRSPEED_CAL_SET.name: TRUE_AIRSPEED_CAL_SET
TRUE_AIRSPEED_CAL_SET.description: Sets airspeed indicators true airspeed reference card (degrees, where 0 is standard sea level conditions)

ANTISKID_BRAKES_TOGGLE.name: ANTISKID_BRAKES_TOGGLE
ANTISKID_BRAKES_TOGGLE.description: Turn the anti-skid braking system on or off.

AXIS_LEFT_BRAKE_SET.name: AXIS_LEFT_BRAKE_SET
AXIS_LEFT_BRAKE_SET.description: Sets left brake position from axis controller (e.g. joystick). -16383 (0 braking) to +16383 (maximum braking)

AXIS_RIGHT_BRAKE_SET.name: AXIS_RIGHT_BRAKE_SET
AXIS_RIGHT_BRAKE_SET.description: Sets right brake position from axis controller (e.g. joystick). -16383 (0 braking) to +16383 (maximum braking)

GEAR_DOWN.name: GEAR_DOWN
GEAR_DOWN.description: Sets gear handle in DOWN position

GEAR_UP.name: GEAR_UP
GEAR_UP.description: Sets gear handle in UP position

RETRACT_FLOAT_SWITCH_DEC.name: RETRACT_FLOAT_SWITCH_DEC
RETRACT_FLOAT_SWITCH_DEC.description: If the plane has retractable floats, moves the retract position from Extend to Neutral, or Neutral to Retract.

RETRACT_FLOAT_SWITCH_INC.name: RETRACT_FLOAT_SWITCH_INC
RETRACT_FLOAT_SWITCH_INC.description: If the plane has retractable floats, moves the retract position from Retract to Neutral, or Neutral to Extend.

BLEED_AIR_SOURCE_CONTROL_INC.name: BLEED_AIR_SOURCE_CONTROL_INC
BLEED_AIR_SOURCE_CONTROL_INC.description: Increases the bleed air source control.

BLEED_AIR_SOURCE_CONTROL_DEC.name: BLEED_AIR_SOURCE_CONTROL_DEC
BLEED_AIR_SOURCE_CONTROL_DEC.description: Decreases the bleed air source control.

BLEED_AIR_SOURCE_CONTROL_SET.name: BLEED_AIR_SOURCE_CONTROL_SET
BLEED_AIR_SOURCE_CONTROL_SET.description: Set to one of: 0: auto1: off2: apu3: engines

CABIN_NO_SMOKING_ALERT_SWITCH_TOGGLE.name: CABIN_NO_SMOKING_ALERT_SWITCH_TOGGLE
CABIN_NO_SMOKING_ALERT_SWITCH_TOGGLE.description: Turn the "No smoking" alert on or off.

CABIN_SEATBELTS_ALERT_SWITCH_TOGGLE.name: CABIN_SEATBELTS_ALERT_SWITCH_TOGGLE
CABIN_SEATBELTS_ALERT_SWITCH_TOGGLE.description: Turn the "Fasten seatbelts" alert on or off.

EXTINGUISH_ENGINE_FIRE.name: EXTINGUISH_ENGINE_FIRE
EXTINGUISH_ENGINE_FIRE.description: Takes a two digit argument.The first digit represents the fire extinguisher index, and the second represents the engine index.For example, 11 would represent using bottle 1 on engine 1. 21 would represent using bottle 2 on engine 1. Typical entries for a twin engine aircraft would be 11 and 22.

HYDRAULIC_SWITCH_TOGGLE.name: HYDRAULIC_SWITCH_TOGGLE
HYDRAULIC_SWITCH_TOGGLE.description: Turn the hydraulic switch on or off.

RELEASE_DROPPABLE_OBJECTS.name: RELEASE_DROPPABLE_OBJECTS
RELEASE_DROPPABLE_OBJECTS.description: Release one dropable object. Multiple key events will release multiple objects.

TOW_PLANE_REQUEST.name: TOW_PLANE_REQUEST
TOW_PLANE_REQUEST.description: Request a tow plane. The user aircraft must be tow-able, stationary, on the ground and not already attached for this to succeed.

SET_TAIL_HOOK_HANDLE.name: SET_TAIL_HOOK_HANDLE
SET_TAIL_HOOK_HANDLE.description:
Sets the tail hook handle. Takes one of the following values:
          
            1 - set tail hook
            0 - retract tail hook

SET_WING_FOLD.name: SET_WING_FOLD
SET_WING_FOLD.description:
Sets the wings into the folded position suitable for storage, typically on a carrier. Takes one of the following values:
          
            1 -fold wings
            0 - unfold wings

TOGGLE_AIRCRAFT_EXIT.name: TOGGLE_AIRCRAFT_EXIT
TOGGLE_AIRCRAFT_EXIT.description: Toggles primary door open/close. Usually follow by (for example) KEY_SELECT_2, etc... for subsequent doors.

TOGGLE_WATER_BALLAST_VALVE.name: TOGGLE_WATER_BALLAST_VALVE
TOGGLE_WATER_BALLAST_VALVE.description: Turn the water ballast valve on or off.

TOW_PLANE_RELEASE.name: TOW_PLANE_RELEASE
TOW_PLANE_RELEASE.description: Release a towed aircraft, usually a glider.

KEY_TUG_HEADING.name: KEY_TUG_HEADING
KEY_TUG_HEADING.description: Triggers tug and sets the desired heading. The units are a 32 bit integer (0 to 4294967295) which represent 0 to 360 degrees. To set a 45 degree angle, for example, set the value to 4294967295 / 8.

KEY_TUG_SPEED.name: KEY_TUG_SPEED
KEY_TUG_SPEED.description: Triggers tug, and sets desired speed, in feet per second. The speed can be either positive (forward movement) or negative (backward movement).

PRESSURIZATION_PRESSURE_ALT_INC.name: PRESSURIZATION_PRESSURE_ALT_INC
PRESSURIZATION_PRESSURE_ALT_INC.description: Increases the altitude that the cabin is pressurized to.

PRESSURIZATION_PRESSURE_ALT_DEC.name: PRESSURIZATION_PRESSURE_ALT_DEC
PRESSURIZATION_PRESSURE_ALT_DEC.description: Decreases the altitude that the cabin is pressurized to.

PRESSURIZATION_CLIMB_RATE_INC.name: PRESSURIZATION_CLIMB_RATE_INC
PRESSURIZATION_CLIMB_RATE_INC.description: Sets the rate at which cabin pressurization is increased.

PRESSURIZATION_CLIMB_RATE_DEC.name: PRESSURIZATION_CLIMB_RATE_DEC
PRESSURIZATION_CLIMB_RATE_DEC.description: Sets the rate at which cabin pressurization is decreased.

PRESSURIZATION_PRESSURE_DUMP_SWTICH.name: PRESSURIZATION_PRESSURE_DUMP_SWTICH
PRESSURIZATION_PRESSURE_DUMP_SWTICH.description: Sets the cabin pressure to the outside air pressure.

STEERING_INC.name: STEERING_INC
STEERING_INC.description: Increments the nose wheel steering position by 5 percent.

STEERING_DEC.name: STEERING_DEC
STEERING_DEC.description: Decrements the nose wheel steering position by 5 percent.

STEERING_SET.name: STEERING_SET
STEERING_SET.description: Sets the value of the nose wheel steering position. Zero is straight ahead(-16383, far left +16383, far right).

TAKEOFF_ASSIST_ARM_TOGGLE.name: TAKEOFF_ASSIST_ARM_TOGGLE
TAKEOFF_ASSIST_ARM_TOGGLE.description: Deploy or remove the assist arm. Refer to the document Notes on Aircraft Systems.

TAKEOFF_ASSIST_ARM_SET.name: TAKEOFF_ASSIST_ARM_SET
TAKEOFF_ASSIST_ARM_SET.description: Value: TRUE request set FALSE request unset

TAKEOFF_ASSIST_FIRE.name: TAKEOFF_ASSIST_FIRE
TAKEOFF_ASSIST_FIRE.description: If everything is set up correctly. Launch from the catapult.

TOGGLE_LAUNCH_BAR_SWITCH.name: TOGGLE_LAUNCH_BAR_SWITCH
TOGGLE_LAUNCH_BAR_SWITCH.description: Toggle the request for the launch bar to be installed or removed.

SET_LAUNCH_BAR_SWITCH.name: SET_LAUNCH_BAR_SWITCH
SET_LAUNCH_BAR_SWITCH.description: Value: TRUE request set FALSE request unset

ROTOR_CLUTCH_SWITCH_TOGGLE.name: ROTOR_CLUTCH_SWITCH_TOGGLE
ROTOR_CLUTCH_SWITCH_TOGGLE.description: Toggles on electric rotor clutch switch

ROTOR_CLUTCH_SWITCH_SET.name: ROTOR_CLUTCH_SWITCH_SET
ROTOR_CLUTCH_SWITCH_SET.description: Sets electric rotor clutch switch on/off (1,0)

ROTOR_GOV_SWITCH_TOGGLE.name: ROTOR_GOV_SWITCH_TOGGLE
ROTOR_GOV_SWITCH_TOGGLE.description: Toggles the electric rotor governor switch

ROTOR_GOV_SWITCH_SET.name: ROTOR_GOV_SWITCH_SET
ROTOR_GOV_SWITCH_SET.description: Sets the electric rotor governor switch on/off (1,0)

ROTOR_LATERAL_TRIM_SET.name: ROTOR_LATERAL_TRIM_SET
ROTOR_LATERAL_TRIM_SET.description: Sets the lateral (right) rotor trim (0 to 16383)

SLING_PICKUP_RELEASE.name: SLING_PICKUP_RELEASE
SLING_PICKUP_RELEASE.description: Toggle between pickup and release mode. Hold mode is automatic and cannot be selected.

HOIST_SWITCH_EXTEND.name: HOIST_SWITCH_EXTEND
HOIST_SWITCH_EXTEND.description: The rate at which a hoist cable extends (set in the Aircraft Configuration File)

HOIST_SWITCH_RETRACT.name: HOIST_SWITCH_RETRACT
HOIST_SWITCH_RETRACT.description: The rate at which a hoist cable retracts (set in the Aircraft Configuration File).

HOIST_SWITCH_SET.name: HOIST_SWITCH_SET
HOIST_SWITCH_SET.description:
The hoist control switch setting. Should be set to one of the following values:
          
            <0 up
            0 off
            >0 down

HOIST_DEPLOY_TOGGLE.name: HOIST_DEPLOY_TOGGLE
HOIST_DEPLOY_TOGGLE.description: Toggles the hoist arm switch, extend or retract.

HOIST_DEPLOY_SET.name: HOIST_DEPLOY_SET
HOIST_DEPLOY_SET.description:
The hoist deployment setting. The value should be set to one of the following:
          
            0 - set hoist switch to retract the arm
            1 - set hoist switch to extend the arm

ADF.name: ADF
ADF.description: Sequentially selects the ADF tuner digits for use with +/-. Follow by SELECT_2 for ADF 2.

ADF_ACTIVE_SET.name: ADF_ACTIVE_SET
ADF_ACTIVE_SET.description: Sets ADF 1 active frequency (BCD16 encoded Hz)

ADF_FRACT_DEC_CARRY.name: ADF_FRACT_DEC_CARRY
ADF_FRACT_DEC_CARRY.description: Decrements ADF 1 frequency by 0.1 KHz, with carry

ADF_FRACT_INC_CARRY.name: ADF_FRACT_INC_CARRY
ADF_FRACT_INC_CARRY.description: Increments ADF 1 frequency by 0.1 KHz, with carry

ADF_HIGHRANGE_SET.name: ADF_HIGHRANGE_SET
ADF_HIGHRANGE_SET.description: Sets ADF highrange frequency (BCD encoded Hz)

ADF_LOWRANGE_SET.name: ADF_LOWRANGE_SET
ADF_LOWRANGE_SET.description: Sets ADF lowrange frequency (BCD encoded Hz)

ADF_STBY_SET.name: ADF_STBY_SET
ADF_STBY_SET.description: Sets ADF standby frequency (BCD16 encoded Hz)

ADF1_WHOLE_DEC.name: ADF1_WHOLE_DEC
ADF1_WHOLE_DEC.description: Decrements ADF 1 by 1 KHz, with carry as digits wrap.

ADF1_WHOLE_INC.name: ADF1_WHOLE_INC
ADF1_WHOLE_INC.description: Increments ADF 1 by 1 KHz, with carry as digits wrap.

ADF1_RADIO_SWAP.name: ADF1_RADIO_SWAP
ADF1_RADIO_SWAP.description: Swaps betweent the ADF 1 frequency and the Standby frequency.

ADF2_100_DEC.name: ADF2_100_DEC
ADF2_100_DEC.description: Decrements the ADF 2 frequency 100 digit, with wrapping

ADF2_10_DEC.name: ADF2_10_DEC
ADF2_10_DEC.description: Decrements the ADF 2 frequency 10 digit, with wrapping

ADF2_1_DEC.name: ADF2_1_DEC
ADF2_1_DEC.description: Decrements the ADF 2 frequency 1 digit, with wrapping

ADF2_100_INC.name: ADF2_100_INC
ADF2_100_INC.description: Increments the ADF 2 frequency 100 digit, with wrapping

ADF2_10_INC.name: ADF2_10_INC
ADF2_10_INC.description: Increments the ADF 2 frequency 10 digit, with wrapping

ADF2_1_INC.name: ADF2_1_INC
ADF2_1_INC.description: Increments the ADF 2 frequency 1 digit, with wrapping

ADF2_ACTIVE_SET.name: ADF2_ACTIVE_SET
ADF2_ACTIVE_SET.description: Sets ADF 2 active frequency (BCD16 encoded Hz)

ADF2_FRACT_INC_CARRY.name: ADF2_FRACT_INC_CARRY
ADF2_FRACT_INC_CARRY.description: Increments ADF 2 frequency by 0.1 KHz, with carry

ADF2_FRACT_DEC_CARRY.name: ADF2_FRACT_DEC_CARRY
ADF2_FRACT_DEC_CARRY.description: Decrements ADF 2 frequency by 0.1 KHz, with carry

ADF2_RADIO_SWAP.name: ADF2_RADIO_SWAP
ADF2_RADIO_SWAP.description: Swaps betweent the ADF 2 frequency and the Standby frequency.

ADF2_RADIO_TENTHS_INC.name: ADF2_RADIO_TENTHS_INC
ADF2_RADIO_TENTHS_INC.description: Increments ADF 2 frequency 1/10 digit, with wrapping

ADF2_RADIO_TENTHS_DEC.name: ADF2_RADIO_TENTHS_DEC
ADF2_RADIO_TENTHS_DEC.description: Decrements ADF 2 frequency 1/10 digit, with wrapping

ADF2_STBY_SET.name: ADF2_STBY_SET
ADF2_STBY_SET.description: Sets ADF 2 standby frequency (BCD16 encoded Hz)

ADF2_WHOLE_DEC.name: ADF2_WHOLE_DEC
ADF2_WHOLE_DEC.description: Decrements ADF 2 by 1 KHz, with carry as digits wrap.

ADF2_WHOLE_INC.name: ADF2_WHOLE_INC
ADF2_WHOLE_INC.description: Increments ADF 2 by 1 KHz, with carry as digits wrap.

AVIONICS_MASTER_SET.name: AVIONICS_MASTER_SET
AVIONICS_MASTER_SET.description: Sets the avionics master switch to on or off.

AVIONICS_MASTER_1_ON.name: AVIONICS_MASTER_1_ON
AVIONICS_MASTER_1_ON.description: Sets avionics master 1 switch to on.

AVIONICS_MASTER_1_OFF.name: AVIONICS_MASTER_1_OFF
AVIONICS_MASTER_1_OFF.description: Sets avionics master 1 switch to off.

AVIONICS_MASTER_1_SET.name: AVIONICS_MASTER_1_SET
AVIONICS_MASTER_1_SET.description: Sets avionics master 1 switch to on or off.

AVIONICS_MASTER_2_ON.name: AVIONICS_MASTER_2_ON
AVIONICS_MASTER_2_ON.description: Sets avionics master 2 switch to on.

AVIONICS_MASTER_2_OFF.name: AVIONICS_MASTER_2_OFF
AVIONICS_MASTER_2_OFF.description: Sets avionics master 2 switch to off.

AVIONICS_MASTER_2_SET.name: AVIONICS_MASTER_2_SET
AVIONICS_MASTER_2_SET.description: Sets the avionics 2 master switch to on or off.

COM_RADIO.name: COM_RADIO
COM_RADIO.description: Sequentially selects the COM tuner digits for use with +/-. Follow by SELECT_2 for COM 2.

COM_RADIO_FRACT_DEC.name: COM_RADIO_FRACT_DEC
COM_RADIO_FRACT_DEC.description: Decrements COM 1 frequency by 25 KHz, with no carry when digit wraps

COM_RADIO_FRACT_DEC_CARRY.name: COM_RADIO_FRACT_DEC_CARRY
COM_RADIO_FRACT_DEC_CARRY.description: Decrement COM 1 frequency by 25 KHz, and carry when digit wraps

COM_RADIO_FRACT_INC.name: COM_RADIO_FRACT_INC
COM_RADIO_FRACT_INC.description: Increment COM 1 frequency by 25 KHz, with no carry when digit wraps

COM_RADIO_FRACT_INC_CARRY.name: COM_RADIO_FRACT_INC_CARRY
COM_RADIO_FRACT_INC_CARRY.description: Increment COM 1 frequency by 25 KHz, and carry when digit wraps

COM_STBY_RADIO_SET.name: COM_STBY_RADIO_SET
COM_STBY_RADIO_SET.description: Sets COM 1 standby frequency (BCD16 encoded Hz)

COM_STBY_RADIO_SWAP.name: COM_STBY_RADIO_SWAP
COM_STBY_RADIO_SWAP.description: Swaps COM 1 frequency with standby frequency.

COM_RADIO_WHOLE_DEC.name: COM_RADIO_WHOLE_DEC
COM_RADIO_WHOLE_DEC.description: Decrement COM 1 frequency by 1 MHz, with no carry when digit wraps

COM_RADIO_WHOLE_INC.name: COM_RADIO_WHOLE_INC
COM_RADIO_WHOLE_INC.description: Increment COM 1 frequency by 1 MHz, with no carry when digit wraps

COM_RECEIVE_ALL_SET.name: COM_RECEIVE_ALL_SET
COM_RECEIVE_ALL_SET.description: Sets whether to receive on all COM radios (1,0)

COM_RECEIVE_ALL_TOGGLE.name: COM_RECEIVE_ALL_TOGGLE
COM_RECEIVE_ALL_TOGGLE.description: Toggles all COM radios to receive on

COM1_STORED_FREQUENCY_SET.name: COM1_STORED_FREQUENCY_SET
COM1_STORED_FREQUENCY_SET.description: Sets COM 1 stored frequency (BCD16 encoded Hz)

COM2_RADIO_FRACT_DEC.name: COM2_RADIO_FRACT_DEC
COM2_RADIO_FRACT_DEC.description: Decrement COM 2 frequency by 25 KHz, with no carry when digit wraps

COM2_RADIO_FRACT_DEC_CARRY.name: COM2_RADIO_FRACT_DEC_CARRY
COM2_RADIO_FRACT_DEC_CARRY.description: Decrement COM 2 frequency by 25 KHz, and carry when digit wraps

COM2_RADIO_FRACT_INC.name: COM2_RADIO_FRACT_INC
COM2_RADIO_FRACT_INC.description: Increment COM 2 frequency by 25 KHz, with no carry when digit wraps

COM2_RADIO_FRACT_INC_CARRY.name: COM2_RADIO_FRACT_INC_CARRY
COM2_RADIO_FRACT_INC_CARRY.description: Increment COM 2 frequency by 25 KHz, and carry when digit wraps

COM2_RADIO_WHOLE_DEC.name: COM2_RADIO_WHOLE_DEC
COM2_RADIO_WHOLE_DEC.description: Decrement COM 2 frequency by 1 MHz, with no carry when digit wraps

COM2_RADIO_WHOLE_INC.name: COM2_RADIO_WHOLE_INC
COM2_RADIO_WHOLE_INC.description: Increment COM 2 frequency by 1 MHz, with no carry when digit wraps

COM2_STBY_RADIO_SET.name: COM2_STBY_RADIO_SET
COM2_STBY_RADIO_SET.description: Sets COM 2 standby frequency (BCD encoded Hz)

COM2_STORED_FREQUENCY_SET.name: COM2_STORED_FREQUENCY_SET
COM2_STORED_FREQUENCY_SET.description: Sets COM 2 stored frequency (BCD16 encoded Hz)

COM3_RADIO_FRACT_DEC.name: COM3_RADIO_FRACT_DEC
COM3_RADIO_FRACT_DEC.description: Decrements COM 3 frequency by 25 KHz, with no carry when digit wraps

COM3_RADIO_FRACT_DEC_CARRY.name: COM3_RADIO_FRACT_DEC_CARRY
COM3_RADIO_FRACT_DEC_CARRY.description: Decrement COM 3 frequency by 25 KHz, and carry when digit wraps.

COM3_RADIO_FRACT_INC.name: COM3_RADIO_FRACT_INC
COM3_RADIO_FRACT_INC.description: Increment COM 3 frequency by 25 KHz, with no carry when digit wraps.

COM3_RADIO_FRACT_INC_CARRY.name: COM3_RADIO_FRACT_INC_CARRY
COM3_RADIO_FRACT_INC_CARRY.description: Increment COM 3 frequency by 25 KHz, and carry when digit wraps.

COM3_RADIO_WHOLE_DEC.name: COM3_RADIO_WHOLE_DEC
COM3_RADIO_WHOLE_DEC.description: Decrement COM 3 frequency by 1 MHz, with no carry when digit wraps

COM3_RADIO_WHOLE_INC.name: COM3_RADIO_WHOLE_INC
COM3_RADIO_WHOLE_INC.description: Increment COM 3 frequency by 1 MHz, with no carry when digit wraps

COM3_STBY_RADIO_SET.name: COM3_STBY_RADIO_SET
COM3_STBY_RADIO_SET.description: Sets COM 3 standby frequency (BCD16 encoded Hz)

COM3_STORED_FREQUENCY_SET.name: COM3_STORED_FREQUENCY_SET
COM3_STORED_FREQUENCY_SET.description: Sets COM 3 stored frequency (BCD16 encoded Hz)

DME.name: DME
DME.description: Selects the DME for use with +/-

DME_SELECT.name: DME_SELECT
DME_SELECT.description: Selects one of the two DME systems (1,2).

RADIO_SELECTED_DME_IDENT_ENABLE.name: RADIO_SELECTED_DME_IDENT_ENABLE
RADIO_SELECTED_DME_IDENT_ENABLE.description: Turns on the identification sound for the selected DME.

RADIO_SELECTED_DME_IDENT_DISABLE.name: RADIO_SELECTED_DME_IDENT_DISABLE
RADIO_SELECTED_DME_IDENT_DISABLE.description: Turns off the identification sound for the selected DME.

RADIO_SELECTED_DME_IDENT_SET.name: RADIO_SELECTED_DME_IDENT_SET
RADIO_SELECTED_DME_IDENT_SET.description: Sets the DME identification sound to the given filename.

RADIO_SELECTED_DME_IDENT_TOGGLE.name: RADIO_SELECTED_DME_IDENT_TOGGLE
RADIO_SELECTED_DME_IDENT_TOGGLE.description: Turns on or off the identification sound for the selected DME.

GPS_CLEAR_BUTTON.name: GPS_CLEAR_BUTTON
GPS_CLEAR_BUTTON.description: Clears entered data on a page

GPS_CLEAR_BUTTON_DOWN.name: GPS_CLEAR_BUTTON_DOWN
GPS_CLEAR_BUTTON_DOWN.description: Triggers the pressing of the Clear button

GPS_CLEAR_BUTTON_UP.name: GPS_CLEAR_BUTTON_UP
GPS_CLEAR_BUTTON_UP.description: Triggers the release of the Clear button.

GPS_MENU_BUTTON.name: GPS_MENU_BUTTON
GPS_MENU_BUTTON.description: Brings up page to select active legs in a flightplan.

GPS_MSG_BUTTON_DOWN.name: GPS_MSG_BUTTON_DOWN
GPS_MSG_BUTTON_DOWN.description: Triggers the pressing of the message button.

GPS_MSG_BUTTON_UP.name: GPS_MSG_BUTTON_UP
GPS_MSG_BUTTON_UP.description: Triggers the release of the message button

GPS_TERRAIN_BUTTON.name: GPS_TERRAIN_BUTTON
GPS_TERRAIN_BUTTON.description: Displays terrain information on default display

TOGGLE_GPS_DRIVES_NAV1.name: TOGGLE_GPS_DRIVES_NAV1
TOGGLE_GPS_DRIVES_NAV1.description: Toggles between GPS and NAV 1 driving NAV 1 OBS display (and AP)

FREQUENCY_SWAP.name: FREQUENCY_SWAP
FREQUENCY_SWAP.description: Swaps frequency with standby on whichever NAV or COM radio is selected.

MARKER_SOUND_SET.name: MARKER_SOUND_SET
MARKER_SOUND_SET.description:
Sets marker beacon sound (1, 0).
          Not currently used in the simulation.

NAV_RADIO.name: NAV_RADIO
NAV_RADIO.description: Sequentially selects the NAV tuner digits for use with +/-. Follow by SELECT_2 for NAV 2.

NAV1_RADIO_FRACT_DEC_CARRY.name: NAV1_RADIO_FRACT_DEC_CARRY
NAV1_RADIO_FRACT_DEC_CARRY.description: Decrement NAV 1 frequency by 50 KHz, and carry when digit wraps

NAV1_RADIO_FRACT_INC_CARRY.name: NAV1_RADIO_FRACT_INC_CARRY
NAV1_RADIO_FRACT_INC_CARRY.description: Increment NAV 1 frequency by 50 KHz, and carry when digit wraps

NAV1_STBY_SET.name: NAV1_STBY_SET
NAV1_STBY_SET.description: Sets NAV 1 standby frequency (BCD16 encoded Hz)

NAV2_RADIO_FRACT_DEC_CARRY.name: NAV2_RADIO_FRACT_DEC_CARRY
NAV2_RADIO_FRACT_DEC_CARRY.description: Decrement NAV 2 frequency by 50 KHz, and carry when digit wraps

NAV2_RADIO_FRACT_INC_CARRY.name: NAV2_RADIO_FRACT_INC_CARRY
NAV2_RADIO_FRACT_INC_CARRY.description: Increment NAV 2 frequency by 50 KHz, and carry when digit wraps

NAV2_STBY_SET.name: NAV2_STBY_SET
NAV2_STBY_SET.description: Sets NAV 2 standby frequency (BCD16 encoded Hz)

NAV3_STBY_SET.name: NAV3_STBY_SET
NAV3_STBY_SET.description: Sets NAV 3 standby frequency (BCD16 encoded Hz)

NAV3_RADIO_SWAP.name: NAV3_RADIO_SWAP
NAV3_RADIO_SWAP.description: Swap between NAV 3 frequency and the standby frequency.

VOR_OBS.name: VOR_OBS
VOR_OBS.description: Sequentially selects the VOR OBS for use with +/-. Follow by KEY_SELECT_2 for VOR 2.

XPNDR.name: XPNDR
XPNDR.description: Sequentially selects the transponder digits for use with +/-.

XPNDR_DEC_CARRY.name: XPNDR_DEC_CARRY
XPNDR_DEC_CARRY.description: Decrements fourth digit of transponder, and with carry.

XPNDR_INC_CARRY.name: XPNDR_INC_CARRY
XPNDR_INC_CARRY.description: Increments fourth digit of transponder, and with carry.

XPNDR_IDENT_OFF.name: XPNDR_IDENT_OFF
XPNDR_IDENT_OFF.description: Disable the transponder Ident (can be used along with the simvar TRANSPONDER_IDENT).

XPNDR_IDENT_ON.name: XPNDR_IDENT_ON
XPNDR_IDENT_ON.description: Enable the transponder Ident (can be used along with the simvar TRANSPONDER_IDENT). After 18 seconds it will disable automatically.

XPNDR_IDENT_SET.name: XPNDR_IDENT_SET
XPNDR_IDENT_SET.description: Set the transponder Ident on or off (can be used along with the simvar TRANSPONDER_IDENT). If set to on, it will switch off automatically after 18 seconds.

XPNDR_IDENT_TOGGLE.name: XPNDR_IDENT_TOGGLE
XPNDR_IDENT_TOGGLE.description: Toggle the transponder Ident from on to off or off to on (can be used along with the simvar TRANSPONDER_IDENT).

CROSS_FEED_OPEN.name: CROSS_FEED_OPEN
CROSS_FEED_OPEN.description: Opens cross feed valve (when used in conjunction with "isolate" tank)

CROSS_FEED_TOGGLE.name: CROSS_FEED_TOGGLE
CROSS_FEED_TOGGLE.description: Toggles crossfeed valve (when used in conjunction with "isolate" tank)

CROSS_FEED_OFF.name: CROSS_FEED_OFF
CROSS_FEED_OFF.description: Closes crossfeed valve (when used in conjunction with "isolate" tank)

CROSS_FEED_LEFT_TO_RIGHT.name: CROSS_FEED_LEFT_TO_RIGHT
CROSS_FEED_LEFT_TO_RIGHT.description: Sets the fuel crossfeed to be from left to right.

CROSS_FEED_RIGHT_TO_LEFT.name: CROSS_FEED_RIGHT_TO_LEFT
CROSS_FEED_RIGHT_TO_LEFT.description: Sets the fuel crossfeed to be from right to left.

FUEL_SELECTOR_2_LEFT.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_2_LEFT
FUEL_SELECTOR_2_LEFT.description: Turns selector 2 to LEFT position (fuel will be retrieved from Left Tip then Left Aux then Left Main).

FUEL_SELECTOR_2_LEFT_AUX.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_2_LEFT_AUX
FUEL_SELECTOR_2_LEFT_AUX.description: Turns selector 2 to LEFT AUX position.

FUEL_SELECTOR_2_LEFT_MAIN.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_2_LEFT_MAIN
FUEL_SELECTOR_2_LEFT_MAIN.description: Sets the fuel selector for engine 2 to the left Main tank.

FUEL_SELECTOR_2_RIGHT.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_2_RIGHT
FUEL_SELECTOR_2_RIGHT.description: Turns selector 2 to RIGHT position (fuel will be retrieved from Right Tip then Right Aux then Right Main)

FUEL_SELECTOR_2_RIGHT_AUX.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_2_RIGHT_AUX
FUEL_SELECTOR_2_RIGHT_AUX.description: Turns selector 2 to RIGHT AUX position.

FUEL_SELECTOR_2_RIGHT_MAIN.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_2_RIGHT_MAIN
FUEL_SELECTOR_2_RIGHT_MAIN.description: Sets the fuel selector for engine 2 to the right Main tank.

FUEL_SELECTOR_2_SET.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_2_SET
FUEL_SELECTOR_2_SET.description: Sets selector 2 position (see the Fuel Selector Codes list for the correct code to use).

FUEL_SELECTOR_3_LEFT.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_3_LEFT
FUEL_SELECTOR_3_LEFT.description: Turns selector 3 to LEFT position (fuel will be retrieved from Left Tip then Left Aux then Left Main).

FUEL_SELECTOR_3_LEFT_AUX.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_3_LEFT_AUX
FUEL_SELECTOR_3_LEFT_AUX.description: Turns selector 3 to LEFT AUX position.

FUEL_SELECTOR_3_LEFT_MAIN.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_3_LEFT_MAIN
FUEL_SELECTOR_3_LEFT_MAIN.description: Sets the fuel selector for engine 3 to the left Main tank.

FUEL_SELECTOR_3_RIGHT.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_3_RIGHT
FUEL_SELECTOR_3_RIGHT.description: Turns selector 3 to RIGHT position (fuel will be retrieved from Right Tip then Right Aux then Right Main).

FUEL_SELECTOR_3_RIGHT_AUX.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_3_RIGHT_AUX
FUEL_SELECTOR_3_RIGHT_AUX.description: Turns selector 3 to RIGHT AUX position.

FUEL_SELECTOR_3_RIGHT_MAIN.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_3_RIGHT_MAIN
FUEL_SELECTOR_3_RIGHT_MAIN.description: Sets the fuel selector for engine 3 to the right Main tank.

FUEL_SELECTOR_3_SET.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_3_SET
FUEL_SELECTOR_3_SET.description: Sets selector 3 position (see the Fuel Selector Codes list for the correct code to use).

FUEL_SELECTOR_4_LEFT.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_4_LEFT
FUEL_SELECTOR_4_LEFT.description: Turns selector 4 to LEFT position (fuel will be retrieved from Left Tip then Left Aux then Left Main).

FUEL_SELECTOR_4_LEFT_AUX.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_4_LEFT_AUX
FUEL_SELECTOR_4_LEFT_AUX.description: Turns selector 4 to LEFT AUX position.

FUEL_SELECTOR_4_LEFT_MAIN.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_4_LEFT_MAIN
FUEL_SELECTOR_4_LEFT_MAIN.description: Sets the fuel selector for engine 4 to the left Main tank.

FUEL_SELECTOR_4_RIGHT.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_4_RIGHT
FUEL_SELECTOR_4_RIGHT.description: Turns selector 4 to RIGHT position (fuel will be retrieved from Right Tip then Right Aux then Right Main).

FUEL_SELECTOR_4_RIGHT_AUX.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_4_RIGHT_AUX
FUEL_SELECTOR_4_RIGHT_AUX.description: Turns selector 4 to RIGHT AUX position.

FUEL_SELECTOR_4_RIGHT_MAIN.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_4_RIGHT_MAIN
FUEL_SELECTOR_4_RIGHT_MAIN.description: Sets the fuel selector for engine 4 to the right Main tank.

FUEL_SELECTOR_4_SET.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_4_SET
FUEL_SELECTOR_4_SET.description: Sets selector 4 position (see the Fuel Selector Codes list for the correct code to use).

FUEL_SELECTOR_ALL.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_ALL
FUEL_SELECTOR_ALL.description: Turn fuel selector 1 to the ALL position.

FUEL_SELECTOR_LEFT.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_LEFT
FUEL_SELECTOR_LEFT.description: Turns selector 1 to LEFT position (fuel will be retrieved from Left Tip then Left Aux then Left Main).

FUEL_SELECTOR_LEFT_AUX.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_LEFT_AUX
FUEL_SELECTOR_LEFT_AUX.description: Turns selector 1 to LEFT AUX position.

FUEL_SELECTOR_LEFT_MAIN.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_LEFT_MAIN
FUEL_SELECTOR_LEFT_MAIN.description: Sets the fuel selector for engine 1 to the left Main tank.

FUEL_SELECTOR_OFF.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_OFF
FUEL_SELECTOR_OFF.description: Turn fuel selector 1 to the OFF position.

FUEL_SELECTOR_RIGHT.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_RIGHT
FUEL_SELECTOR_RIGHT.description: Turns selector 1 to RIGHT position (fuel will be retrieved from Right Tip then Right Aux then Right Main).

FUEL_SELECTOR_RIGHT_AUX.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_RIGHT_AUX
FUEL_SELECTOR_RIGHT_AUX.description: Turns selector 1 to RIGHT AUX position.

FUEL_SELECTOR_RIGHT_MAIN.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_RIGHT_MAIN
FUEL_SELECTOR_RIGHT_MAIN.description: Sets the fuel selector for engine 1 to the right Main tank.

FUEL_SELECTOR_SET.name: FUEL_SELECTOR_SET
FUEL_SELECTOR_SET.description: Sets selector 1 position (see the Fuel Selector Codes list for the correct code to use).

FUELSYSTEM_JUNCTION_SET.name: FUELSYSTEM_JUNCTION_SET
FUELSYSTEM_JUNCTION_SET.description: Set the current junction options for which lines are open or closed at any given time. This event requires two parameters: the first is the index of the junction (as defined by the N index of the Junction.N parameter), and the second is the Option index, which is what sets the lines to open/close.

FUELSYSTEM_PUMP_OFF.name: FUELSYSTEM_PUMP_OFF
FUELSYSTEM_PUMP_OFF.description: Turn a fuel pump off. The event requires the N index of the Pump.N parameter to define the pump to use.

FUELSYSTEM_PUMP_ON.name: FUELSYSTEM_PUMP_ON
FUELSYSTEM_PUMP_ON.description: Turn a fuel pump on. The event requires the N index of the Pump.N parameter to define the pump to use.

FUELSYSTEM_PUMP_SET.name: FUELSYSTEM_PUMP_SET
FUELSYSTEM_PUMP_SET.description: Set a fuel pump to be either on or off. The event requires the N index of the Pump.N parameter to define the pump to use.

FUELSYSTEM_PUMP_TOGGLE.name: FUELSYSTEM_PUMP_TOGGLE
FUELSYSTEM_PUMP_TOGGLE.description: Toggle a fuel pump on/off. The event requires the N index of the Pump.N parameter to define the pump to use.

FUELSYSTEM_TRIGGER_OFF.name: FUELSYSTEM_TRIGGER_OFF
FUELSYSTEM_TRIGGER_OFF.description: Turn a trigger event off. The event requires the N index of the Trigger.N parameter to define the trigger to switch off.

FUELSYSTEM_TRIGGER_ON.name: FUELSYSTEM_TRIGGER_ON
FUELSYSTEM_TRIGGER_ON.description: Turn a trigger event on. The event requires the N index of the Trigger.N parameter to define the trigger to switch on.

FUELSYSTEM_TRIGGER_SET.name: FUELSYSTEM_TRIGGER_SET
FUELSYSTEM_TRIGGER_SET.description: Set a trigger event to be either on or off. The event requires the N index of the Trigger.N parameter to define the trigger to set.

FUELSYSTEM_TRIGGER_TOGGLE.name: FUELSYSTEM_TRIGGER_TOGGLE
FUELSYSTEM_TRIGGER_TOGGLE.description: Toggle a trigger event on/off. The event requires the N index of the Trigger.N parameter to define the trigger to toggle.

FUELSYSTEM_VALVE_CLOSE.name: FUELSYSTEM_VALVE_CLOSE
FUELSYSTEM_VALVE_CLOSE.description: Close a specific valve in the fuel system. The event requires the N index of the Valve.N parameter to define the valve to target.

FUELSYSTEM_VALVE_OPEN.name: FUELSYSTEM_VALVE_OPEN
FUELSYSTEM_VALVE_OPEN.description: Open a specific valve in the fuel system. The event requires the N index of the Valve.N parameter to define the valve to target.

FUELSYSTEM_VALVE_SET.name: FUELSYSTEM_VALVE_SET
FUELSYSTEM_VALVE_SET.description: Set a valve to be either open or closed. The event requires the N index of the Valve.N parameter to define the valve to target.

FUELSYSTEM_VALVE_TOGGLE.name: FUELSYSTEM_VALVE_TOGGLE
FUELSYSTEM_VALVE_TOGGLE.description: Toggle a valve open/closed. The event requires the N index of the Valve.N parameter to define the valve to target.

SET_FUEL_TRANSFER_CUSTOM.name: SET_FUEL_TRANSFER_CUSTOM
SET_FUEL_TRANSFER_CUSTOM.description: Set the fuel transfer mode to the "custom" setting. Requires that at least 1 transfer pump has been defined in the flight_model.cfg file using the fuel_transfer_pump.N parameter.

FUEL_TRANSFER_CUSTOM_INDEX_TOGGLE.name: FUEL_TRANSFER_CUSTOM_INDEX_TOGGLE
FUEL_TRANSFER_CUSTOM_INDEX_TOGGLE.description: Toggle a custom fuel transfer pump on/off. The index is the Pump ID value supplied as part of the fuel pump definition for the fuel_transfer_pump.N parameter in the flight_model.cfg file.

SET_FUEL_TRANSFER_FORWARD.name: SET_FUEL_TRANSFER_FORWARD
SET_FUEL_TRANSFER_FORWARD.description: Set the fuel transfer system to use the "forward" setting, which pumps from tank 1 to tank 2.

SET_FUEL_TRANSFER_AFT.name: SET_FUEL_TRANSFER_AFT
SET_FUEL_TRANSFER_AFT.description: Set the fuel transfer system to use the "aft" setting, which pumps from tank 2 to tank 1.

SET_FUEL_TRANSFER_AUTO.name: SET_FUEL_TRANSFER_AUTO
SET_FUEL_TRANSFER_AUTO.description: Set the fuel transfer pump to automatically balance the fuel in tanks 1 and 2 to maintain the CG.

SET_FUEL_TRANSFER_OFF.name: SET_FUEL_TRANSFER_OFF
SET_FUEL_TRANSFER_OFF.description: Set the fuel transfer pump to off.

ADD_FUEL_QUANTITY.name: ADD_FUEL_QUANTITY
ADD_FUEL_QUANTITY.description: Adds fuel to the aircraft, 25% of capacity by default. 0 to 65535 (max fuel) can be passed.

ELECT_FUEL_PUMP1_SET.name: ELECT_FUEL_PUMP1_SET
ELECT_FUEL_PUMP1_SET.description:
Set the electrical pump status for engines 1-4. Values are as follows:
          
            0 = Off
            1 = On
            2 = Auto
          
          These keys are only useful when using the legacy [FUEL] system.

ENGINE_FUELFLOW_BUG_POSITION1.name: ENGINE_FUELFLOW_BUG_POSITION1
ENGINE_FUELFLOW_BUG_POSITION1.description: Not currently used in the simulation.

FUEL_DUMP_SWITCH_SET.name: FUEL_DUMP_SWITCH_SET
FUEL_DUMP_SWITCH_SET.description:
Set to 1 (TRUE) or 0 (FALSE). The switch can only be set to TRUE if fuel_dump_rate is specified in the aircraft configuration file, indicating that a fuel dump system exists.
          This key is only useful when using the legacy [FUEL] system.

FUEL_DUMP_TOGGLE.name: FUEL_DUMP_TOGGLE
FUEL_DUMP_TOGGLE.description:
Used to turn on (1, TRUE) or off (0, FALSE) the fuel dump switch.
          This key is only useful when using the legacy [FUEL] system.

MANUAL_FUEL_PRESSURE_PUMP.name: MANUAL_FUEL_PRESSURE_PUMP
MANUAL_FUEL_PRESSURE_PUMP.description: Activate the manual fuel pressure pump. Used for both modern [FUEL_SYSTEM] and legacy [FUEL] systems.

MANUAL_FUEL_PRESSURE_PUMP_SET.name: MANUAL_FUEL_PRESSURE_PUMP_SET
MANUAL_FUEL_PRESSURE_PUMP_SET.description: Set the position of the fuel manual pump handle, as a percentage. This key is only useful when using the modern [FUEL_SYSTEM].

MANUAL_FUEL_TRANSFER.name: MANUAL_FUEL_TRANSFER
MANUAL_FUEL_TRANSFER.description: When set to 1 (TRUE) it sets the fuel transfer mode to manual.

RELEASE_DROP_TANK_ALL.name: RELEASE_DROP_TANK_ALL
RELEASE_DROP_TANK_ALL.description: Release all external tanks that can be jettisoned.

RELEASE_DROP_TANK_1.name: RELEASE_DROP_TANK_1
RELEASE_DROP_TANK_1.description: Release the first external tank that can be jettisoned.

RELEASE_DROP_TANK_2.name: RELEASE_DROP_TANK_2
RELEASE_DROP_TANK_2.description: Release the second external tank that can be jettisoned.

REPAIR_AND_REFUEL.name: REPAIR_AND_REFUEL
REPAIR_AND_REFUEL.description: Fully repair and refuel the user aircraft. Ignored if flight realism is enforced.

REQUEST_FUEL_KEY.name: REQUEST_FUEL_KEY
REQUEST_FUEL_KEY.description: Request a fuel truck. The aircraft must be in a parking spot for this to be successful.

ANTIDETONATION_TANK_VALVE_TOGGLE.name: ANTIDETONATION_TANK_VALVE_TOGGLE
ANTIDETONATION_TANK_VALVE_TOGGLE.description: Toggle the anti-detonation valve. Pass a value to determine which tank to use if there are multiple tanks. See the Fuel Selector Codes list for the correct tank code to use. Note that this key requires the [ANTIDETONATION_SYSTEM.N] system to have been set up in the engine configuration file.

NITROUS_TANK_VALVE_TOGGLE.name: NITROUS_TANK_VALVE_TOGGLE
NITROUS_TANK_VALVE_TOGGLE.description: Toggle the nitrous valve. Pass a value to determine which tank to use if there are multiple tanks. See the Fuel Selector Codes list for the correct tank code to use. Note that this key requires the [NITROUS_SYSTEM.N] system to have been set up in the engine configuration file.

CAPTURE_SCREENSHOT.name: CAPTURE_SCREENSHOT
CAPTURE_SCREENSHOT.description: Capture the current view as a screenshot. Which will be saved to a bmp file in: My Documents\Pictures\

RELOAD_USER_AIRCRAFT.name: RELOAD_USER_AIRCRAFT
RELOAD_USER_AIRCRAFT.description: Reloads the user aircraft data (from cache if same type loaded as an AI,otherwise from disk)

EXTERNAL_SYSTEM_SET.name: EXTERNAL_SYSTEM_SET
EXTERNAL_SYSTEM_SET.description: Generic key event to set a number value.

EXTERNAL_SYSTEM_TOGGLE.name: EXTERNAL_SYSTEM_TOGGLE
EXTERNAL_SYSTEM_TOGGLE.description: Generic key event to toggle a value on/off (true/false).

MINUS.name: MINUS
MINUS.description: Used in conjunction with "selected" parameters to decrease their value (e.g.,radio frequency)

MOUSE_LOOK_TOGGLE.name: MOUSE_LOOK_TOGGLE
MOUSE_LOOK_TOGGLE.description: Switch Mouse Look mode on or off. Mouse Look mode enables a user to control their view using the mouse, and holding down the space bar.

PLUS.name: PLUS
PLUS.description: Used in conjunction with "selected" parameters to increase their value (e.g.,radio frequency)

READOUTS_SLEW.name: READOUTS_SLEW
READOUTS_SLEW.description: Cycle through information readouts while in slew

TOGGLE_AIRPORT_NAME_DISPLAY.name: TOGGLE_AIRPORT_NAME_DISPLAY
TOGGLE_AIRPORT_NAME_DISPLAY.description: Turn on or off the airport name.

TOGGLE_JETWAY.name: TOGGLE_JETWAY
TOGGLE_JETWAY.description: Requests a jetway, which will only be answered if the aircraft is at a parking spot.

VIDEO_RECORD_TOGGLE.name: VIDEO_RECORD_TOGGLE
VIDEO_RECORD_TOGGLE.description: Turn on or off the video recording feature. This records uncompressed AVI format files to: My Documents\Videos\

VIEW_WINDOW_TITLES_TOGGLE.name: VIEW_WINDOW_TITLES_TOGGLE
VIEW_WINDOW_TITLES_TOGGLE.description: Turn window titles on or off.

YAXIS_INVERT_TOGGLE.name: YAXIS_INVERT_TOGGLE
YAXIS_INVERT_TOGGLE.description: Switch inversion of Y axis controls on or off.

FREEZE_LATITUDE_LONGITUDE_TOGGLE.name: FREEZE_LATITUDE_LONGITUDE_TOGGLE
FREEZE_LATITUDE_LONGITUDE_TOGGLE.description: Turns the freezing of the lat/lon position of the aircraft (either user or AI controlled) on or off. If this key event is set, it means that the latitude and longitude of the aircraft are not being controlled by ESP, so enabling, for example, a SimConnect client to control the position of the aircraft. This can also apply to altitude and attitude. Refer to the simulation variables: IS LATITUDE LONGITUDE FREEZE ON, IS ALTITUDE FREEZE ON, and IS ATTITUDE FREEZE ON Refer also to the SimConnect_AIReleaseControl function.

FREEZE_LATITUDE_LONGITUDE_SET.name: FREEZE_LATITUDE_LONGITUDE_SET
FREEZE_LATITUDE_LONGITUDE_SET.description: Freezes the lat/lon position of the aircraft.

FREEZE_ALTITUDE_TOGGLE.name: FREEZE_ALTITUDE_TOGGLE
FREEZE_ALTITUDE_TOGGLE.description: Turns the freezing of the altitude of the aircraft on or off.

FREEZE_ALTITUDE_SET.name: FREEZE_ALTITUDE_SET
FREEZE_ALTITUDE_SET.description: Freezes the altitude of the aircraft.

FREEZE_ATTITUDE_TOGGLE.name: FREEZE_ATTITUDE_TOGGLE
FREEZE_ATTITUDE_TOGGLE.description: Turns the freezing of the attitude (pitch, bank and heading) of the aircraft on or off.

FREEZE_ATTITUDE_SET.name: FREEZE_ATTITUDE_SET
FREEZE_ATTITUDE_SET.description: Freezes the attitude (pitch, bank and heading) of the aircraft.

POINT_OF_INTEREST_TOGGLE_POINTER.name: POINT_OF_INTEREST_TOGGLE_POINTER
POINT_OF_INTEREST_TOGGLE_POINTER.description: Turn the point-of-interest indicator (often a light beam) on or off. Refer to the Missions system documentation.

POINT_OF_INTEREST_CYCLE_PREVIOUS.name: POINT_OF_INTEREST_CYCLE_PREVIOUS
POINT_OF_INTEREST_CYCLE_PREVIOUS.description: Change the current point-of-interest to the previous point-of-interest.

POINT_OF_INTEREST_CYCLE_NEXT.name: POINT_OF_INTEREST_CYCLE_NEXT
POINT_OF_INTEREST_CYCLE_NEXT.description: Change the current point-of-interest to the next point-of-interest.

MP_TRANSFER_CONTROL.name: MP_TRANSFER_CONTROL
MP_TRANSFER_CONTROL.description: Toggle to the next player to track

MP_PLAYER_CYCLE.name: MP_PLAYER_CYCLE
MP_PLAYER_CYCLE.description: Cycle through the current user aircraft.

MP_PLAYER_FOLLOW.name: MP_PLAYER_FOLLOW
MP_PLAYER_FOLLOW.description: Set the view to follow the selected user aircraft.

MP_VOICE_CAPTURE_START.name: MP_VOICE_CAPTURE_START
MP_VOICE_CAPTURE_START.description: Start capturing audio from the users computer and transmitting it to all other players in the multiplayer session who are turned to the same radio frequency.

MP_BROADCAST_VOICE_CAPTURE_START.name: MP_BROADCAST_VOICE_CAPTURE_START
MP_BROADCAST_VOICE_CAPTURE_START.description: Start capturing audio from the users computer and transmitting it to all other players in the multiplayer session.

TOGGLE_RACERESULTS_WINDOW.name: TOGGLE_RACERESULTS_WINDOW
TOGGLE_RACERESULTS_WINDOW.description: Show or hide multi-player race results.

SIM_RATE.name: SIM_RATE
SIM_RATE.description: Selects the simulation rate. Use the PLUS and MINUS events to increment/decrement the value.

SIM_RATE_DECR.name: SIM_RATE_DECR
SIM_RATE_DECR.description: Decreases the simulation rate, which will slow down the in-simulation time.

SIM_RATE_INCR.name: SIM_RATE_INCR
SIM_RATE_INCR.description: Increase the simulation rate, which will speed up the in-simulation time.

AXIS_PAN_PITCH.name: AXIS_PAN_PITCH
AXIS_PAN_PITCH.description: Sets the pitch of the camera axis. Requires an angle.

AXIS_PAN_HEADING.name: AXIS_PAN_HEADING
AXIS_PAN_HEADING.description: Sets the heading of the axis. Requires an angle.

AXIS_PAN_TILT.name: AXIS_PAN_TILT
AXIS_PAN_TILT.description: Sets the tilt of the axis. Requires an angle.

VIEW_CHASE_DISTANCE_ADD.name: VIEW_CHASE_DISTANCE_ADD
VIEW_CHASE_DISTANCE_ADD.description: Increments the distance of the view camera from the chase object (such as in Spot Plane view, or viewing an AI controlled aircraft).

VIEW_CHASE_DISTANCE_SUB.name: VIEW_CHASE_DISTANCE_SUB
VIEW_CHASE_DISTANCE_SUB.description: Decrements the distance of the view camera from the chase object.

MAP_ZOOM_FINE_OUT.name: MAP_ZOOM_FINE_OUT
MAP_ZOOM_FINE_OUT.description: Fine zoom out in map view

VIEW_COCKPIT_FORWARD.name: VIEW_COCKPIT_FORWARD
VIEW_COCKPIT_FORWARD.description: Switch immediately to the forward view, in 2D mode.

VIEW_FORWARD_LEFT.name: VIEW_FORWARD_LEFT
VIEW_FORWARD_LEFT.description: Sets view direction forward and left

VIEW_FORWARD_RIGHT.name: VIEW_FORWARD_RIGHT
VIEW_FORWARD_RIGHT.description: Sets view direction forward and right

VIEW_FORWARD_RIGHT_UP.name: VIEW_FORWARD_RIGHT_UP
VIEW_FORWARD_RIGHT_UP.description: Sets view forward, right, and up

VIEW_FORWARD_LEFT_UP.name: VIEW_FORWARD_LEFT_UP
VIEW_FORWARD_LEFT_UP.description: Sets view forward left and up

VIEW_LEFT.name: VIEW_LEFT
VIEW_LEFT.description: Sets view direction to the left

VIEW_LINKING_SET.name: VIEW_LINKING_SET
VIEW_LINKING_SET.description: Links all the views from one camera together, so that panning the view will change the view of all the linked cameras.

VIEW_LINKING_TOGGLE.name: VIEW_LINKING_TOGGLE
VIEW_LINKING_TOGGLE.description: Turns view linking on or off.

VIEW_PANEL_ALPHA_SELECT.name: VIEW_PANEL_ALPHA_SELECT
VIEW_PANEL_ALPHA_SELECT.description: Sets the mode to change the alpha-blending, so the keys KEY_PLUS and KEY_MINUS increment and decrement the value.

VIEW_PANEL_ALPHA_SET.name: VIEW_PANEL_ALPHA_SET
VIEW_PANEL_ALPHA_SET.description: Sets the alpha-blending value for the panel. Takes a parameter in the range 0to 255. The alpha-blending can be changed from the keyboard using Ctrl-Shift-T,and the plus and minus keys.

VIEW_REAR.name: VIEW_REAR
VIEW_REAR.description: Sets view direction to the rear

VIEW_REAR_LEFT.name: VIEW_REAR_LEFT
VIEW_REAR_LEFT.description: Sets view direction to the rear and left

VIEW_REAR_LEFT_UP.name: VIEW_REAR_LEFT_UP
VIEW_REAR_LEFT_UP.description: Sets view rear left and up

VIEW_REAR_RIGHT.name: VIEW_REAR_RIGHT
VIEW_REAR_RIGHT.description: Sets view direction to the rear and right

VIEW_REAR_RIGHT_UP.name: VIEW_REAR_RIGHT_UP
VIEW_REAR_RIGHT_UP.description: Sets view rear, right, and up

VIEW_RESET.name: VIEW_RESET
VIEW_RESET.description: Resets the view to the default

VIEW_RIGHT.name: VIEW_RIGHT
VIEW_RIGHT.description: Sets view direction to the right

VIEW_VIRTUAL_COCKPIT_FORWARD.name: VIEW_VIRTUAL_COCKPIT_FORWARD
VIEW_VIRTUAL_COCKPIT_FORWARD.description: Switch immediately to the forward view, in virtual cockpit mode.

PAN_RESET_COCKPIT.name: PAN_RESET_COCKPIT
PAN_RESET_COCKPIT.description: Reset panning to forward, if in cockpit view
